1
00:00:10,219 --> 00:00:12,382
My name is Talal Mustafa al-Shuweimi

2
00:00:12,555 --> 00:00:15,710
I’m from Raqqa Province, living on Sajiyah Street

3
00:00:17,570 --> 00:00:19,476
I’m 45 years old

4
00:00:21,703 --> 00:00:25,906
I have 3 wives and 13 children

5
00:00:29,679 --> 00:00:34,405
During the Assad regime’s control of Raqqa, I worked at the Water Department

6
00:00:35,336 --> 00:00:37,901
After the problems and battles started

7
00:00:39,699 --> 00:00:41,375
I was dismissed from work

8
00:00:42,789 --> 00:00:45,307
The regime accused me of being a terrorist

9
00:00:45,820 --> 00:00:48,437
The Air Force Intelligence raided my house

10
00:00:49,070 --> 00:00:50,461
Because they claimed I was a terrorist

11
00:00:50,902 --> 00:00:52,469
The dismissal order came from Damascus

12
00:00:52,477 --> 00:00:53,477
Of course

13
00:00:53,765 --> 00:00:55,807
It was all a malicious report

14
00:00:56,929 --> 00:00:59,359
Because we were locals and stayed in the city

15
00:01:00,889 --> 00:01:04,115
My dismissal order came in 2012

16
00:01:04,906 --> 00:01:07,599
So I fled Raqqa for a while

17
00:01:07,719 --> 00:01:08,844
And my brother was arrested

18
00:01:09,547 --> 00:01:10,797
By the Assad regime

19
00:01:11,679 --> 00:01:12,922
On behalf of the regime

20
00:01:13,258 --> 00:01:17,609
They put him in Sednaya Prison for about 6 years

21
00:01:19,929 --> 00:01:24,804
After they detained my brother for 6 years in prison

22
00:01:27,108 --> 00:01:29,148
The Free Syrian Army entered Raqqa

23
00:01:29,172 --> 00:01:31,773
I was already dismissed from work as a “terrorist”

24
00:01:32,219 --> 00:01:35,039
About 6 or 7 months after the FSA entered

25
00:01:35,445 --> 00:01:40,126
ISIS entered the city, calling itself the Islamic State

26
00:01:41,179 --> 00:01:43,617
They took control of the area

27
00:01:44,351 --> 00:01:47,648
Within their first 2 or 3 months of settling in

28
00:01:48,344 --> 00:01:53,101
They arrested me, accusing me of being a regime agent—a <i>shabiha</i> [pro-regime thug]

29
00:01:54,758 --> 00:02:01,031
They detained me at Point 11, with the security members

30
00:02:01,469 --> 00:02:03,402
Inside the former Governor’s Palace

31
00:02:03,672 --> 00:02:05,707
I stayed there for about a week

32
00:02:06,794 --> 00:02:08,664
After the Governor’s Palace, they took me

33
00:02:09,648 --> 00:02:14,414
To a new security base near the National Hospital area in Raqqa

34
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:17,606
It was inside the old Military Judiciary building of the Assad regime

35
00:02:19,289 --> 00:02:23,113
A week later, they moved me from the Governor’s Palace basement

36
00:02:23,893 --> 00:02:27,324
To the old Military Judiciary building near the Traffic Circle

37
00:02:27,349 --> 00:02:28,511
I stayed in that base

38
00:02:30,037 --> 00:02:32,112
Under the same charge, regime agent

39
00:02:32,474 --> 00:02:34,519
I stayed there for 53 days

40
00:02:34,646 --> 00:02:36,240
After 53 days

41
00:02:37,402 --> 00:02:40,409
They released me because there was no evidence against me

42
00:02:40,654 --> 00:02:43,912
The one who interrogated me

43
00:02:44,763 --> 00:02:47,404
Was from Raqqa Province, from Tabqa city

44
00:02:48,308 --> 00:02:49,612
His family name was Khameesi

45
00:02:50,459 --> 00:02:52,019
He was called Abu Yousuf, the interrogator

46
00:02:52,146 --> 00:02:53,456
He was the head of interrogators

47
00:02:54,693 --> 00:02:57,518
Another man was nicknamed Abu Abdurrahman

48
00:02:58,865 --> 00:03:01,979
His name was Mahmoud al-Ali al-Sahou from the Ghanem al-Zahir clan

49
00:03:02,224 --> 00:03:03,815
From an area called al-Jaif

50
00:03:04,217 --> 00:03:07,224
East of the al-Eywij area

51
00:03:07,795 --> 00:03:09,604
Near Rashid Farm in Raqqa

52
00:03:11,310 --> 00:03:15,146
I stayed under interrogation for about 53 days

53
00:03:15,171 --> 00:03:19,053
After they confirmed there was nothing against me

54
00:03:19,162 --> 00:03:22,576
They realized I’d already been dismissed by the Assad regime as a “terrorist”

55
00:03:22,901 --> 00:03:24,197
So they released me

56
00:03:24,623 --> 00:03:26,916
And gave me a clearance card

57
00:03:28,224 --> 00:03:30,379
A certificate proving there were no charges against me

58
00:03:30,404 --> 00:03:34,431
As a Syrian citizen

59
00:03:34,717 --> 00:03:35,722
And a Sunni by faith

60
00:03:35,747 --> 00:03:38,989
I went back to work with the other workers

61
00:03:39,888 --> 00:03:42,521
Trying to earn a living to support my children

62
00:03:44,482 --> 00:03:47,403
Around 50 or 60 days after returning

63
00:03:48,138 --> 00:03:49,248
I was surprised to see someone

64
00:03:49,740 --> 00:03:55,303
Sadly, he was from the same neighborhood, Sunni, and a local of the area

65
00:03:56,287 --> 00:03:57,902
His name was Mahmoud al-Shahada

66
00:03:58,974 --> 00:04:00,769
He was an ISIS emir overseeing the Water Department

67
00:04:00,794 --> 00:04:02,107
His name was Mahmoud al-Shahada

68
00:04:02,404 --> 00:04:03,810
Nicknamed Abu Hudhayfa

69
00:04:03,896 --> 00:04:07,795
Abu Hudhayfa had been detained in Assad regime prisons back in 2000

70
00:04:07,834 --> 00:04:09,209
Accused of joining Jund al-Sham

71
00:04:10,271 --> 00:04:14,193
He struck a deal with the regime in Sednaya Prison and was released

72
00:04:14,303 --> 00:04:18,201
Then brought to Raqqa and appointed as an emir in the caliphate

73
00:04:18,898 --> 00:04:24,935
Mahmoud al-Shahada, known as Abu Hudhayfa, and his brother were both active and skilled

74
00:04:25,217 --> 00:04:26,732
His brother’s name was Hassan

75
00:04:27,123 --> 00:04:28,934
He had two brothers, Hassan and Hassaan

76
00:04:28,959 --> 00:04:31,719
His brother was an emir and his right-hand man

77
00:04:32,404 --> 00:04:34,600
When I came back to the Water Department

78
00:04:35,696 --> 00:04:39,818
I was surprised he’d become the department’s emir after being released from Sednaya

79
00:04:40,037 --> 00:04:43,443
When the workers learned I was coming to work again

80
00:04:43,468 --> 00:04:47,998
I had no salary, but people gave us charity for the children

81
00:04:48,199 --> 00:04:51,364
They offered us odd jobs outside

82
00:04:51,389 --> 00:04:55,303
Of course, we had no fixed income since I and others were dismissed from work

83
00:04:56,357 --> 00:04:58,639
Then Abu Hudhayfa came

84
00:05:00,212 --> 00:05:02,906
And arrested me himself—Mahmoud al-Shahada

85
00:05:03,703 --> 00:05:08,006
By then, he’d become “Minister of the Caliphate” because of his influence and knowledge

86
00:05:08,537 --> 00:05:11,120
He had many initiatives, so he arrested me

87
00:05:11,443 --> 00:05:13,808
He tricked me into it

88
00:05:14,959 --> 00:05:17,404
At the time, we were fixing a broken water line

89
00:05:17,474 --> 00:05:20,206
In the Khasra Faraj area, and when we came

90
00:05:21,089 --> 00:05:24,584
He said, “The sheikh wants to see you”

91
00:05:24,608 --> 00:05:29,959
“He wants to ask a few questions, and there’s also a broken pipe at the security point”

92
00:05:30,467 --> 00:05:33,998
He said, “You should fix it.” I said, “As you wish, Abu Hudhayfa”

93
00:05:34,495 --> 00:05:41,615
When I arrived there, I only saw weapons pointed at me

94
00:05:41,685 --> 00:05:45,123
They threw me to the ground, stepped on my neck, and arrested me

95
00:05:45,494 --> 00:05:47,025
For about two months

96
00:05:47,799 --> 00:05:50,006
When I returned to work at the Water Department

97
00:05:50,670 --> 00:05:52,607
Abu Hudhayfa grabbed me by the hair

98
00:05:52,990 --> 00:05:54,334
Dragged me toward the table

99
00:05:54,670 --> 00:05:56,217
Pressed my head onto it

100
00:05:56,498 --> 00:05:59,381
And placed his foot on my left shoulder

101
00:05:59,967 --> 00:06:04,084
He said to me, “You’re a shabih (pro-regime thug). You shouldn’t enter the institution. You’re an agent for the regime”

102
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:09,602
I told him, Calm down, Sheikh, this is my clearance from Point 11, and I’m clean, there’s nothing against me

103
00:06:09,927 --> 00:06:12,170
I have children, but he said, No, you’re a shabih

104
00:06:12,740 --> 00:06:14,896
And no one will be able to get you back to work

105
00:06:16,188 --> 00:06:20,719
We brought mediations from one sheikh and another, but nothing worked

106
00:06:21,501 --> 00:06:23,842
At that point, I had a small amount of money

107
00:06:24,052 --> 00:06:26,373
And my brother had about 125,000 Syrian pounds

108
00:06:26,701 --> 00:06:28,248
So I bought a taxi

109
00:06:28,935 --> 00:06:30,459
A taxi with no official papers

110
00:06:30,484 --> 00:06:33,229
Back then they used to call it “<i>Arouriya</i>”

111
00:06:33,254 --> 00:06:37,435
Because it was stolen—they’d steal and sell it without papers

112
00:06:37,804 --> 00:06:39,404
So they called it an “<i>Arouriya</i> car”

113
00:06:40,638 --> 00:06:43,654
I worked as a taxi driver

114
00:06:44,427 --> 00:06:46,523
For about 5 to 6 months

115
00:06:47,492 --> 00:06:49,326
One day

116
00:06:51,873 --> 00:06:54,170
The Hisba (religious police) raided me at my home

117
00:06:56,248 --> 00:06:57,693
On 16th Street

118
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:03,101
They said to me, You’re a man who trades cigarettes

119
00:07:03,724 --> 00:07:05,818
And they detained me for 4 days

120
00:07:07,763 --> 00:07:13,101
They insulted me, but it wasn’t severe or extreme

121
00:07:13,443 --> 00:07:15,719
They kept saying, You’re a cigarette dealer, and so on

122
00:07:16,021 --> 00:07:21,568
I told him, Sheikh, I’m not a cigarette dealer, I don’t even smoke cigarettes, but yes, I smoke hookah

123
00:07:22,373 --> 00:07:23,709
Yes, I smoke hookah

124
00:07:24,521 --> 00:07:28,206
But I don’t smoke cigarettes. If I did, I’d tell you

125
00:07:28,810 --> 00:07:30,193
Anyway, they detained me

126
00:07:30,865 --> 00:07:31,865
One man

127
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:35,302
And took me to a Hisba base called “Panorama”

128
00:07:36,201 --> 00:07:39,310
It’s in Raqqa, near Maqs Roundabout, called “Panorama”

129
00:07:39,724 --> 00:07:42,520
There was a Hisba base there. The emir in charge was Abu Bishr

130
00:07:42,545 --> 00:07:44,146
Abu Bishr, a Saudi national

131
00:07:45,388 --> 00:07:47,208
After 4 days of detention

132
00:07:49,091 --> 00:07:53,269
I moved my home to another neighborhood, fearing someone was targeting me

133
00:07:53,294 --> 00:07:57,810
I was hungry, and I had 12 or 13 children

134
00:07:59,145 --> 00:08:00,364
There was no strength left in me

135
00:08:02,310 --> 00:08:06,106
I thought, There are people who trade cigarettes and make a living from it

136
00:08:06,856 --> 00:08:10,786
So I started selling cigarettes. Honestly, the accusation already stuck to me anyway

137
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:14,067
So I decided to trade cigarettes

138
00:08:14,981 --> 00:08:16,356
And I began working in that trade

139
00:08:17,060 --> 00:08:19,123
For about a month or a month and a half

140
00:08:20,052 --> 00:08:23,005
Then a Hisba patrol came and arrested me

141
00:08:23,669 --> 00:08:26,450
They detained me for about 15 days

142
00:08:27,645 --> 00:08:28,912
And the one who arrested me

143
00:08:29,942 --> 00:08:35,528
Was a man from Rumaila named Mustafa al-Hamid al-Muslih

144
00:08:36,341 --> 00:08:37,934
Known as Abu Seif Maqs

145
00:08:38,583 --> 00:08:41,333
He also had another nom de guerre, Abu Seif Doshka

146
00:08:42,026 --> 00:08:43,799
Also known as Abu Seif Maqs

147
00:08:43,958 --> 00:08:47,489
He was originally from the Wahb clan

148
00:08:47,880 --> 00:08:51,302
His maternal uncles were from the Masaar group of the Barij clan

149
00:08:52,216 --> 00:08:54,591
As for Abu Seif Maqs, his past

150
00:08:56,450 --> 00:08:58,018
Was extremely bad

151
00:08:58,747 --> 00:09:02,114
He used to take hashish and pills and was unemployed

152
00:09:02,864 --> 00:09:05,560
And strangely enough

153
00:09:06,224 --> 00:09:09,877
When ISIS entered, I was shocked to see he had become a Doshka gunner

154
00:09:09,893 --> 00:09:13,036
Then, since he was from the area and knew people

155
00:09:13,528 --> 00:09:16,911
They made him emir of the Search and Investigation Unit, this man called Mustafa

156
00:09:17,919 --> 00:09:19,692
Mustafa arrested me

157
00:09:20,341 --> 00:09:24,630
For the second time, for about 15 days. He tortured, beat, and insulted me

158
00:09:25,122 --> 00:09:26,802
Of course, they found no cigarettes with me

159
00:09:28,239 --> 00:09:32,849
The emir of the Search Unit was the same Mustafa al-Muslih

160
00:09:33,638 --> 00:09:34,828
Known as Abu Seif

161
00:09:34,950 --> 00:09:39,724
And another man called Ibrahim al-Ali al-Khayheet

162
00:09:40,466 --> 00:09:44,515
From the Ghanem al-Zahir clan, living near the Jazra Junction in Raqqa

163
00:09:46,052 --> 00:09:47,802
Known as Abu Hudhayfa

164
00:09:48,669 --> 00:09:51,005
Abu Hudhayfa was about 30 years old

165
00:09:51,575 --> 00:09:55,145
The sharia official was Abu Hamza al-Tunsi

166
00:09:56,435 --> 00:09:59,406
There was another man, originally from Sukhna, living on Sajiyah Street in Raqqa

167
00:09:59,685 --> 00:10:00,716
Named Abu Zayd

168
00:10:01,450 --> 00:10:03,841
His brother was the emir of the Islamic Police

169
00:10:04,023 --> 00:10:06,843
In Raqqa Province, overseeing the whole wilaya

170
00:10:07,083 --> 00:10:08,786
Abu Zayd was a sharia official

171
00:10:08,844 --> 00:10:12,125
Second in rank under Abu Hamza al-Tunsi

172
00:10:12,226 --> 00:10:18,044
He worked as a messenger between the court and the Hisba’s sharia office

173
00:10:19,286 --> 00:10:21,645
As for how many times I was imprisoned

174
00:10:21,670 --> 00:10:27,505
If I tried to describe my suffering, I’d need 3 months to finish

175
00:10:27,810 --> 00:10:31,231
The torture and misery we endured

176
00:10:31,661 --> 00:10:34,935
I was imprisoned 28 times

177
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:38,890
Some people might think I’m lying, but the locals know me well

178
00:10:39,052 --> 00:10:43,296
My bag was always ready, because every 2 or 3 days ISIS would arrest me

179
00:10:43,740 --> 00:10:47,515
The first time I was jailed in a security checkpoint, the charge was suspicion

180
00:10:47,763 --> 00:10:50,255
I was imprisoned there for 56 days

181
00:10:50,786 --> 00:10:55,802
The other 27 times were all for cigarette trading

182
00:10:56,794 --> 00:11:00,872
My detentions ranged between 10 to 15 days, sometimes up to 2 months

183
00:11:01,028 --> 00:11:05,996
Then they’d release me, since they found no evidence, and I was very cautious around them

184
00:11:06,544 --> 00:11:08,052
The last time

185
00:11:09,443 --> 00:11:10,443
They

186
00:11:11,325 --> 00:11:15,325
Launched a campaign against cigarette sellers, and ISIS members specifically targeted me

187
00:11:15,567 --> 00:11:19,512
Me and 2 or 3 other people

188
00:11:19,739 --> 00:11:22,403
7 people, including me, were sentenced to <i>qisas</i> [execution by retribution]

189
00:11:22,898 --> 00:11:24,410
They sentenced them to <i>qisas</i> with me too

190
00:11:26,590 --> 00:11:28,778
They summoned me and took me by deceit

191
00:11:30,114 --> 00:11:31,692
They tricked me and took me away

192
00:11:33,723 --> 00:11:38,112
They called me on the phone and said, Are you Talal al-Shuweimi? I said, Yes, I am Talal al-Shuweimi

193
00:11:38,137 --> 00:11:40,145
They said, Someone confessed against you

194
00:11:40,762 --> 00:11:43,004
He said you sold him 2 cartons of cigarettes

195
00:11:44,285 --> 00:11:46,746
That wasn’t true at all

196
00:11:46,771 --> 00:11:49,895
Because I hadn’t personally sold cigarettes for about a year

197
00:11:50,316 --> 00:11:52,731
Yes, I was a cigarette dealer

198
00:11:54,004 --> 00:11:55,004
But

199
00:11:55,285 --> 00:11:58,417
When I was in the trade, I didn’t distribute or sell cigarettes myself

200
00:11:59,340 --> 00:12:01,028
I didn’t distribute or sell them

201
00:12:02,004 --> 00:12:04,410
When they summoned me, I told them, I’ll come right away

202
00:12:04,738 --> 00:12:09,496
I got in my car and went to the Hisba, which was at the end of Sajiyah Street

203
00:12:10,279 --> 00:12:12,464
On Atiya Bakery Street

204
00:12:13,303 --> 00:12:15,644
And the Hisba emir who was on Sajiyah Street

205
00:12:15,761 --> 00:12:19,738
Was named Issa, from the Jais clan, known as Abu Humam

206
00:12:20,566 --> 00:12:22,207
And Abu Humam, before that

207
00:12:22,527 --> 00:12:27,246
Had been a sergeant in the Political Security branch under the Assad regime

208
00:12:28,809 --> 00:12:32,504
When he was a sergeant under the Assad regime and ISIS was established

209
00:12:33,129 --> 00:12:38,262
Abu Humam came and announced his defection and joined the Islamic State

210
00:12:41,603 --> 00:12:45,814
When Abu Humam summoned me, he had already raided my house about 10 times

211
00:12:46,231 --> 00:12:51,010
Out of 27 raids, he came several times, knowing they’d never find cigarettes with me

212
00:12:51,331 --> 00:12:55,209
One time he knocked on my door and called out, “Hey Shuweimi!”

213
00:12:55,457 --> 00:12:59,099
Your hookah is running, and we know you don’t have cigarettes, but bring the hookah and come

214
00:12:59,124 --> 00:13:02,317
So I carried the hookah with its coals and placed it in his car

215
00:13:03,215 --> 00:13:05,606
When Abu Humam summoned me, I asked him, Where’s the man?

216
00:13:07,319 --> 00:13:10,819
Who testified against me? He told me, Rest for 5 minutes

217
00:13:12,385 --> 00:13:14,301
Now I’ll call the man

218
00:13:14,981 --> 00:13:17,588
When he called me, he said the man is here with me, come see him

219
00:13:17,613 --> 00:13:19,665
When I went, it turned out there was no man there at all

220
00:13:19,690 --> 00:13:21,621
He said, In 5 minutes he’ll come

221
00:13:21,994 --> 00:13:23,400
So I waited 5 minutes

222
00:13:23,566 --> 00:13:26,209
And said, Abu Humam, where’s the man? He told me, You sold cigarettes

223
00:13:26,226 --> 00:13:27,231
I said, Sheikh

224
00:13:28,051 --> 00:13:31,616
I swore to him by God, and honestly, I swear truthfully, I don’t sell cigarettes

225
00:13:31,973 --> 00:13:35,704
And I don’t distribute cigarettes. I have workers who sell and deliver instead of me

226
00:13:36,777 --> 00:13:38,910
What surprised me was his attitude, and I sat down

227
00:13:39,527 --> 00:13:44,410
I told him, Abu Humam, let me tell you something. Even if I sold two boxes of cigarettes

228
00:13:44,738 --> 00:13:48,191
You’re not smarter than Abu Seif. If he were in your place, he would’ve arrested me right away

229
00:13:49,011 --> 00:13:51,894
The news would’ve reached Abu Seif before it reached you

230
00:13:53,745 --> 00:13:56,660
He said, God willing, and started laughing

231
00:13:57,988 --> 00:14:01,345
Of course he’s ignorant and doesn’t understand religion, and so is Abu Seif

232
00:14:01,370 --> 00:14:05,128
When I quote hadiths to him, he tells me, Fear God for yourself

233
00:14:05,511 --> 00:14:07,788
Even the phrase “Fear God for yourself”

234
00:14:08,199 --> 00:14:12,167
He doesn’t even know what it means. Imagine, when I quoted a hadith to him

235
00:14:12,297 --> 00:14:15,718
He said, Fear God for yourself — meaning he’s ignorant

236
00:14:16,316 --> 00:14:17,877
The word ignorant means lack of knowledge

237
00:14:17,910 --> 00:14:19,314
And Islam is as vast as the sea

238
00:14:19,339 --> 00:14:22,706
Whatever you learn in Islam today is just a drop in that sea

239
00:14:24,175 --> 00:14:26,472
I sat there and was shocked when

240
00:14:26,855 --> 00:14:30,011
Mustafa, known as Abu Seif Maqs, the Emir of the Investigation Unit, entered

241
00:14:30,895 --> 00:14:33,996
And Ibrahim al-Ali al-Khayheet, known as Abu Hudhayfa

242
00:14:34,192 --> 00:14:36,628
Both masked, along with 4 or 5 others

243
00:14:37,050 --> 00:14:39,605
They blindfolded me and tied my hands

244
00:14:40,269 --> 00:14:42,113
And took me to the Investigation Section

245
00:14:42,316 --> 00:14:46,566
Along with 3 or 4 masked members as well

246
00:14:46,785 --> 00:14:48,761
They put me in a small Kia Rio, Korean-made

247
00:14:48,786 --> 00:14:55,603
I knew all their cars and the license plates they used during and after work hours

248
00:14:55,683 --> 00:14:57,167
They put me in the Kia Rio

249
00:14:57,620 --> 00:15:02,520
The moment Abu Seif grabbed me — my beard was long, almost reaching my navel

250
00:15:02,902 --> 00:15:06,535
I hadn’t shaved my beard since 2011

251
00:15:07,956 --> 00:15:11,423
He grabbed my beard violently and started banging my head against the wall

252
00:15:11,535 --> 00:15:14,501
His fingernails dug into my face and blood began to come out

253
00:15:14,683 --> 00:15:16,415
Blood was running from my face

254
00:15:16,900 --> 00:15:19,636
I didn’t feel it at first, but I felt warmth

255
00:15:19,878 --> 00:15:23,696
While blindfolded, I put my hand on my face and found real blood

256
00:15:24,408 --> 00:15:26,972
They took me to the Investigation Section and up to the second floor

257
00:15:29,831 --> 00:15:34,527
They brought me into a room on the second floor, where the Investigation Section was located

258
00:15:35,118 --> 00:15:39,965
It was headed by Abu Hamza al-Tunisi, the senior <i>sharia</i> official and overall emir

259
00:15:39,990 --> 00:15:43,122
Under him were the Emir of Investigation, Abu Seif Maqs, and Abu Hudhayfa

260
00:15:43,676 --> 00:15:46,418
And Abu Zaid, from the Sakhani clan

261
00:15:46,896 --> 00:15:49,549
His brother, Fayez, was the Emir of the Islamic Police

262
00:15:49,574 --> 00:15:51,012
They took me upstairs

263
00:15:51,919 --> 00:15:53,787
My hands were tied behind my back

264
00:15:54,380 --> 00:15:56,987
And I was blindfolded, and they began beating me

265
00:15:57,012 --> 00:16:01,004
They hit me with sticks and metal rods — the beating was extremely painful

266
00:16:02,185 --> 00:16:06,177
I was beaten for 3 days straight

267
00:16:06,985 --> 00:16:10,677
They poured water on me and kept beating me again and again

268
00:16:11,123 --> 00:16:16,110
When I woke up, I found myself hanging on the wall on the second floor

269
00:16:16,498 --> 00:16:22,497
That area was at the start of Sajiyah Street, at the intersection with Hittin School Street

270
00:16:24,107 --> 00:16:26,497
That place was known as the Investigation Zone

271
00:16:26,584 --> 00:16:27,998
I found myself hanging

272
00:16:28,779 --> 00:16:31,497
I remained hanging on the wall for 18 days

273
00:16:33,013 --> 00:16:36,404
It was the middle of the hot summer season

274
00:16:36,927 --> 00:16:40,326
But our Lord, praise be to Him, is merciful in His mercy

275
00:16:40,701 --> 00:16:42,216
And in His glory and majesty

276
00:16:42,685 --> 00:16:45,623
The heat actually helped me endure the beatings and pain

277
00:16:45,648 --> 00:16:50,788
When my body was hot and sweating, the blows hurt less than when it was cold in winter

278
00:16:53,662 --> 00:16:55,794
I suffered terribly from thirst

279
00:16:56,412 --> 00:16:58,865
My toes barely touched the ground

280
00:16:58,890 --> 00:17:02,685
And I could hardly reach a bottle of drink

281
00:17:02,710 --> 00:17:06,230
I would bring it close when they gave me a break to drink, from the intensity of thirst

282
00:17:06,255 --> 00:17:07,559
Because of the severe torture

283
00:17:09,036 --> 00:17:11,107
Once, Abu Seif

284
00:17:15,419 --> 00:17:16,419
Told me

285
00:17:17,021 --> 00:17:21,590
You’re a cigarette dealer. I’ll cut you into pieces, put you in bags, and throw you to the dogs

286
00:17:21,615 --> 00:17:26,427
I told him, I’m a Muslim. Neither you nor anyone else will put me in bags and throw me to the dogs

287
00:17:27,732 --> 00:17:30,413
You want, and I want, but God does what He wants

288
00:17:31,247 --> 00:17:38,333
Then he punched me several times. My ribs were broken, and I was exhausted from the beatings, torture, and humiliation

289
00:17:38,849 --> 00:17:41,333
He said, I’ll bring your wife here

290
00:17:43,101 --> 00:17:45,168
I said, You want to bring my wife?

291
00:17:45,615 --> 00:17:49,804
We were created to defend our land, our honor, and our Islam

292
00:17:50,029 --> 00:17:53,279
Who are you to bring my wife to me? I said that to his face

293
00:17:53,708 --> 00:17:56,005
Exactly like that, and even if he were in front of me now

294
00:17:56,279 --> 00:17:59,324
I would confront him with those same words, and I have proof for everything I say

295
00:17:59,349 --> 00:18:01,387
Without a doubt, and there are witnesses to my words

296
00:18:01,646 --> 00:18:03,746
The first witness is God Almighty

297
00:18:03,771 --> 00:18:07,003
And there are 14 people who can testify to what I said

298
00:18:07,857 --> 00:18:12,497
When he said that, I couldn’t bear the way he talked about my wife

299
00:18:12,724 --> 00:18:14,113
So I cursed him

300
00:18:14,138 --> 00:18:17,877
I cursed his honor, even though it’s forbidden in Islam

301
00:18:17,886 --> 00:18:22,487
But I couldn’t bear it when Abu Seif started insulting my honor

302
00:18:23,496 --> 00:18:26,325
Because Abu Seif was a brutal, ignorant type

303
00:18:27,216 --> 00:18:31,314
He had very little understanding or awareness, as we Arabs say

304
00:18:31,865 --> 00:18:33,904
His mind was dull, and he was stupid in his own way

305
00:18:34,654 --> 00:18:40,391
He brought a big stick, about one meter long, and started beating me on my ribs until they broke

306
00:18:40,416 --> 00:18:43,294
I started spitting blood from my mouth

307
00:18:44,130 --> 00:18:46,816
He hit me and caused about 9 wounds on my head

308
00:18:47,325 --> 00:18:50,615
He also hit me here beside my forehead, leaving two visible wounds to this day

309
00:18:51,529 --> 00:18:53,904
So I was left with 9 wounds on my head

310
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:59,130
Then a Saudi Emir came

311
00:18:59,397 --> 00:19:03,285
May God clothe him with health and reward him, even if he was a member of ISIS

312
00:19:03,310 --> 00:19:06,501
I don’t mean to insult ISIS members in general

313
00:19:07,029 --> 00:19:11,294
Nor to smear their image—except those whom God has spared

314
00:19:11,319 --> 00:19:15,771
There were some who were true Muslims, and when they saw what was happening, they ran away

315
00:19:16,310 --> 00:19:20,424
And some came only to steal, or to distort the image of Islam

316
00:19:20,697 --> 00:19:22,307
And some came for position and power

317
00:19:22,388 --> 00:19:24,107
As for the Saudi, may God guide him

318
00:19:25,536 --> 00:19:30,187
And I pray that my supplication for him reaches the Lord of the Worlds

319
00:19:30,211 --> 00:19:34,718
Because he didn’t help only me; I heard he helped many others too

320
00:19:34,734 --> 00:19:37,685
When he came and saw me hanging in the torture cells

321
00:19:38,952 --> 00:19:41,467
There was also a man with us named Ibrahim al-Fakkash

322
00:19:41,492 --> 00:19:44,927
And another named Ibrahim Ayoub, known as Shantar

323
00:19:44,952 --> 00:19:48,798
And Ibrahim al-Fakkash was nicknamed al-Bariwi. When they saw me being tortured that way

324
00:19:49,536 --> 00:19:51,696
They started screaming and crying for me

325
00:19:53,154 --> 00:19:55,001
And when they began crying for me

326
00:19:56,290 --> 00:20:00,509
The Saudi man—whom I had never met before—heard the shouting and came

327
00:20:01,290 --> 00:20:02,907
He came and unchained me

328
00:20:02,993 --> 00:20:04,793
When he unchained me, Abu Seif came

329
00:20:05,880 --> 00:20:07,805
They argued—who are you, and who sent you?

330
00:20:07,872 --> 00:20:11,193
The Saudi man punched Abu Seif twice and pointed his rifle at him

331
00:20:11,485 --> 00:20:12,485
Then he unchained me

332
00:20:14,189 --> 00:20:15,833
And poured water on me

333
00:20:16,013 --> 00:20:21,029
Then he lowered me to the ground

334
00:20:21,302 --> 00:20:25,185
He and Abu Seif quarreled and complained about each other to the sharia judge

335
00:20:25,201 --> 00:20:27,318
Arguing about how he got in and so on

336
00:20:27,724 --> 00:20:31,458
The second floor was off-limits, reserved for us only

337
00:20:31,739 --> 00:20:38,523
We were sentenced to <i>qisas</i> [execution], and not only us—there were also 5 or 6 women from Raqqa city

338
00:20:38,990 --> 00:20:39,990
From the Rumaila neighborhood

339
00:20:41,771 --> 00:20:45,401
After lowering me, the Saudi man went to bring the sharia committee

340
00:20:46,732 --> 00:20:49,831
And to summon the security and religious officials to show them the torture inside the Hisba prisons

341
00:20:51,169 --> 00:20:52,997
When he came back, they hid me

342
00:20:53,318 --> 00:20:55,839
Every day they hid me in a different prison or location

343
00:20:57,212 --> 00:20:58,821
And one time

344
00:20:59,146 --> 00:21:00,458
They put me in a solitary cell

345
00:21:00,685 --> 00:21:01,966
That solitary cell

346
00:21:03,177 --> 00:21:08,900
Had two walls, one square meter in area, a metal roof, and an iron door

347
00:21:09,724 --> 00:21:11,465
I couldn’t walk

348
00:21:11,490 --> 00:21:15,599
And on top of that, I was chained with iron shackles about one meter long

349
00:21:16,286 --> 00:21:20,325
Tied up, and they would fasten me either to the door itself, its handle, or its ring

350
00:21:20,880 --> 00:21:22,697
Then Abu Zaid, the sharia official, came

351
00:21:25,122 --> 00:21:29,911
May God not prolong his life, nor the lives of his brothers or even his father

352
00:21:29,936 --> 00:21:33,013
Because his father was one of the sheikhs of Raqqa city

353
00:21:33,950 --> 00:21:36,419
One of those sheikhs who change their cloak every day—people with no principles

354
00:21:37,982 --> 00:21:43,106
Abu Zaid came with two other sheikhs, all dressed in white

355
00:21:43,740 --> 00:21:45,816
They carried the air of formal clerics

356
00:21:45,990 --> 00:21:52,060
And I had no strength, relying only on God Almighty and the Quran I held in my hand

357
00:21:53,646 --> 00:21:55,497
He came and said, Prepare yourself

358
00:21:56,271 --> 00:21:59,396
He ordered me to stand, then unlocked my handcuffs and the padlock

359
00:22:00,310 --> 00:22:01,715
He said, Stand

360
00:22:02,443 --> 00:22:06,051
We are going to carry out the <i>hadd</i> [punishment] on you now. Your execution order came today

361
00:22:06,154 --> 00:22:07,708
At 4 p.m.

362
00:22:08,036 --> 00:22:11,880
At the Asr call to prayer, near al-Rahman Mosque intersection on Sajiya Street

363
00:22:14,411 --> 00:22:16,997
The two men with him

364
00:22:18,536 --> 00:22:20,911
Those two were of Saudi origin

365
00:22:23,232 --> 00:22:24,500
They said to him

366
00:22:24,950 --> 00:22:29,396
They said to me, Sheikh, have you repented? I said, Repent from what? Am I an infidel to repent?

367
00:22:30,189 --> 00:22:31,607
Repent from what exactly?

368
00:22:32,974 --> 00:22:35,333
What sin did I commit?

369
00:22:35,833 --> 00:22:37,341
Against the Islamic State?

370
00:22:38,497 --> 00:22:42,626
For what reason does Abu Zaid sentence me to death, and for what crime?

371
00:22:44,325 --> 00:22:46,117
Abu Zaid said to me, Be quiet, be quiet

372
00:22:46,407 --> 00:22:48,786
They told me, You talk too much

373
00:22:49,029 --> 00:22:52,950
They said, You like to talk a lot, and we know you’ve memorized the Book of Monotheism

374
00:22:52,975 --> 00:22:55,126
Yes, I have memorized the Book of Monotheism

375
00:22:56,419 --> 00:23:00,724
I told him, This book of monotheism is not yours—it’s God’s book

376
00:23:00,966 --> 00:23:04,219
And this Quran wasn’t written or revealed by you

377
00:23:04,740 --> 00:23:06,297
So how dare you say that to me

378
00:23:08,529 --> 00:23:12,379
A discussion started between me and him

379
00:23:12,404 --> 00:23:15,997
The other sheikh asked me, and I said, Yes, Sheikh, I used to trade cigarettes

380
00:23:16,716 --> 00:23:19,654
But I repented, and the best of sinners are those who repent

381
00:23:20,661 --> 00:23:24,130
And our Lord, may He be glorified, forgives sins

382
00:23:26,255 --> 00:23:30,316
He began speaking to Abu Zaid, saying, You’re frightening this Muslim man

383
00:23:30,794 --> 00:23:31,809
With execution

384
00:23:32,357 --> 00:23:34,809
He said to him, You people are unjust, and turned against Abu Zaid

385
00:23:35,309 --> 00:23:39,466
He told him, I’ll hold you accountable, Abu Zaid, and I’ll make this man file a complaint against you

386
00:23:39,491 --> 00:23:41,013
We were on the second floor

387
00:23:43,075 --> 00:23:48,575
They argued among themselves, and the man came to me and kissed my forehead

388
00:23:50,497 --> 00:23:53,300
He told me, Rest. God willing, your situation will improve

389
00:23:53,325 --> 00:23:57,136
He asked me, Who beat you like this? I answered, It was Abu Seif and Abu Hudhayfa

390
00:23:58,990 --> 00:24:00,605
After I said that

391
00:24:00,699 --> 00:24:04,496
They came at 11 p.m. and removed my shackles

392
00:24:05,825 --> 00:24:08,263
Then they cuffed my hands behind my back

393
00:24:09,974 --> 00:24:11,918
Once again, Abu Seif with the handcuffs

394
00:24:12,622 --> 00:24:16,583
He grabbed me by the cuffs from above, pulling me up like this

395
00:24:18,263 --> 00:24:19,887
Then lowered me beside the room door

396
00:24:20,075 --> 00:24:22,802
My beard was so long it reached my navel

397
00:24:24,122 --> 00:24:25,816
Now I’ll show you my photo

398
00:24:25,982 --> 00:24:28,808
How I looked with the beard, and how I was sentenced to execution

399
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:35,590
And how ISIS, the so-called Islamic State, kept my record in their archives

400
00:24:35,615 --> 00:24:38,388
And we don’t generalize—only God knows who was righteous among them

401
00:24:39,200 --> 00:24:41,380
Because the fingers of the hand aren’t all the same

402
00:24:41,904 --> 00:24:44,568
Abu Seif wrapped his hand around my beard

403
00:24:45,568 --> 00:24:49,905
He grabbed my beard—it was long—and dragged me by it while my hands were shackled

404
00:24:50,093 --> 00:24:54,187
I was out of breath, but God Almighty gives a person strength

405
00:24:55,388 --> 00:24:57,202
Great and powerful strength

406
00:24:57,919 --> 00:25:02,732
He kept dragging me by my beard, saying, I’ll teach the whole town a lesson through you

407
00:25:05,122 --> 00:25:08,309
He said to me, plainly, “The time of the Prophet is gone”

408
00:25:08,419 --> 00:25:10,678
I told him, Are we now living in Pharaoh’s time?

409
00:25:11,348 --> 00:25:13,497
For you to say the Prophet’s era has passed?

410
00:25:14,059 --> 00:25:18,958
He dragged me by my beard until he brought me to the feet of Ibrahim al-Fakkash

411
00:25:19,399 --> 00:25:20,805
Who was nicknamed al-Bariwi

412
00:25:20,989 --> 00:25:22,700
He was sentenced along with me too

413
00:25:23,020 --> 00:25:27,297
They told us we’d been sentenced to execution, but the ruling hadn’t been carried out yet

414
00:25:28,094 --> 00:25:30,465
He dragged me by my beard, pulling me along the ground

415
00:25:31,231 --> 00:25:34,617
Until we reached the feet of Ibrahim al-Fakkash, nicknamed al-Bariwi

416
00:25:35,044 --> 00:25:36,516
He asked him, Do you know this man?

417
00:25:36,637 --> 00:25:37,719
He replied, Yes, I know him

418
00:25:37,743 --> 00:25:40,762
Abu Seif said to al-Bariwi, This is the clever player, al-Shuweimi

419
00:25:40,950 --> 00:25:44,669
They called me the clever player because they never caught me with cigarettes

420
00:25:44,700 --> 00:25:50,786
I’d been in so many prisons and detentions—arrested 27 times before by the Hisba (religious police)

421
00:25:50,989 --> 00:25:55,215
Once they detained me for security reasons, and another time I spent a month and a half in Point 11

422
00:25:56,161 --> 00:25:58,270
That’s why they gave me that nickname

423
00:25:58,872 --> 00:26:03,591
He dragged me by my beard all that distance, pulled me out of the room again, still dragging me

424
00:26:07,950 --> 00:26:12,536
I stayed with them in the investigation section for about 53 or 54 days

425
00:26:14,029 --> 00:26:15,029
They came

426
00:26:15,926 --> 00:26:18,163
And shackled my hands behind my back again

427
00:26:19,295 --> 00:26:21,716
They took me out after 53 days

428
00:26:21,889 --> 00:26:22,889
And said to me

429
00:26:23,536 --> 00:26:27,310
We’ll spare your neck if you pay a sum of money

430
00:26:28,848 --> 00:26:30,864
In exchange for paying a financial amount

431
00:26:31,311 --> 00:26:36,309
The ruling would be treated like theft but under a religious ruling

432
00:26:36,919 --> 00:26:39,805
In the past, people would say things like, I’ll rob you right before your eyes

433
00:26:40,083 --> 00:26:42,016
My strength and my dignity

434
00:26:42,465 --> 00:26:45,684
They wanted to rob me, but in the name of what the Prophet said—meaning freeing a slave

435
00:26:45,709 --> 00:26:50,161
They asked me, What property do you have? At that time, I owned 6 or 7 cars

436
00:26:50,981 --> 00:26:54,481
Because I worked hard in the cigarette trade

437
00:26:55,262 --> 00:26:58,110
Whether that work was forbidden or not

438
00:26:58,575 --> 00:27:01,144
Some people said it was forbidden, others said it wasn’t

439
00:27:01,169 --> 00:27:06,144
Maybe we were ignorant about it, but we didn’t really know whether it was forbidden or not

440
00:27:06,169 --> 00:27:09,126
The important thing is, I worked hard, forbidden or not

441
00:27:09,317 --> 00:27:11,602
I struggled and earned that money

442
00:27:12,208 --> 00:27:17,493
They took everything I had—gold, silver, and cars

443
00:27:18,094 --> 00:27:19,981
They took everything, even my farmland

444
00:27:20,262 --> 00:27:22,489
I had a deed of ownership from 50 years ago

445
00:27:23,129 --> 00:27:24,875
In my name, inherited from my father

446
00:27:24,900 --> 00:27:29,126
Back then, the Syrian regime used to seize land from people who owned a lot of it

447
00:27:29,645 --> 00:27:33,281
Out of fear, my father registered the land in his sons’ names

448
00:27:33,306 --> 00:27:37,001
He divided the land equally among his sons

449
00:27:38,020 --> 00:27:40,098
So my share was the same as my brothers’

450
00:27:41,103 --> 00:27:43,786
Even the land that was originally my father’s

451
00:27:44,197 --> 00:27:46,059
They made me fingerprint it as sold and bought

452
00:27:46,084 --> 00:27:49,019
I also had a motorbike with two frames at times

453
00:27:49,044 --> 00:27:53,789
I used it around the neighborhood and inside the city during traffic jams and hot weather

454
00:27:53,814 --> 00:27:56,529
They made me fingerprint that as sold and bought too

455
00:28:01,311 --> 00:28:04,923
I was detained many times, and regarding the interrogation sessions

456
00:28:05,491 --> 00:28:10,225
They sometimes lasted long; sometimes they interrogated me, sometimes they didn’t

457
00:28:10,884 --> 00:28:12,756
Just to put psychological pressure on me

458
00:28:12,764 --> 00:28:15,326
My first interrogation was at Point 11

459
00:28:16,197 --> 00:28:20,603
I talked too much during the interrogation because of how unjustly they treated me

460
00:28:21,095 --> 00:28:25,415
I was innocent—I was just trying to earn a living, working as a taxi driver

461
00:28:25,876 --> 00:28:29,150
Because I talked so much, they interrogated me and took me to the judge

462
00:28:29,175 --> 00:28:31,929
Their system was that every week they brought us a blank sheet

463
00:28:31,954 --> 00:28:34,595
We’d write our names, like Talal Mustafa al-Shuweimi

464
00:28:34,907 --> 00:28:37,790
Was he interrogated? If yes, he should write “yes”

465
00:28:38,181 --> 00:28:40,039
If not interrogated, he should write “no”

466
00:28:40,064 --> 00:28:41,900
And was he presented to the judge? “Yes” or “no”

467
00:28:41,925 --> 00:28:46,204
And every time, I wrote “no,” blaming them for my case

468
00:28:47,064 --> 00:28:51,003
Since I had children, no means, and my house was rented in the beginning

469
00:28:52,308 --> 00:28:54,958
Sometimes they’d take me to the prison corridor

470
00:28:55,675 --> 00:28:57,105
At Point 11

471
00:28:58,379 --> 00:29:02,137
They’d leave me for two or three hours, blindfolded

472
00:29:02,731 --> 00:29:03,731
Standing on my feet

473
00:29:04,379 --> 00:29:06,426
Or sitting on the ground

474
00:29:06,598 --> 00:29:08,551
They wouldn’t speak to me or beat me

475
00:29:08,576 --> 00:29:11,870
But I could hear the sounds of torture and beatings in the corridor

476
00:29:11,895 --> 00:29:16,401
They’d shout at the prisoners, Stand up, you dog! Turn around! Lift your foot! They had their own methods of torture

477
00:29:17,198 --> 00:29:24,317
But they didn’t beat me; they just kept me in the corridor blindfolded

478
00:29:24,786 --> 00:29:26,794
Leaving me that way for two or three hours

479
00:29:26,819 --> 00:29:29,232
In the end, he’d say to me, Sheikh

480
00:29:29,257 --> 00:29:34,544
Go back to your group cell. I’d remove the blindfold inside and hand it to him through the window

481
00:29:34,622 --> 00:29:38,262
That happened about 10 times

482
00:29:39,194 --> 00:29:40,512
And the last time

483
00:29:42,629 --> 00:29:47,465
I told them I wanted to be interrogated because I was honestly afraid they’d put me in the corridor again

484
00:29:48,145 --> 00:29:49,809
And one time

485
00:29:49,999 --> 00:29:51,239
I lost my patience

486
00:29:51,551 --> 00:29:53,762
I started crying and said, It’s only one death

487
00:29:53,950 --> 00:29:55,873
A person only dies once

488
00:29:56,833 --> 00:30:00,590
I started crying and shouting, so they blindfolded me and took me away

489
00:30:01,395 --> 00:30:03,325
They took me to the interrogation room

490
00:30:03,934 --> 00:30:05,083
And the interrogator

491
00:30:06,520 --> 00:30:10,129
He died, may God have mercy on him

492
00:30:10,481 --> 00:30:11,825
His name was Abu Abdul Rahman

493
00:30:12,786 --> 00:30:15,301
He was from the Jaif area in Raqqa, from the Ghanem al-Zahir clan

494
00:30:16,739 --> 00:30:18,373
He said to me, Talal al-Shuweimi

495
00:30:21,223 --> 00:30:22,223
You

496
00:30:22,801 --> 00:30:24,246
Are you still doing amulet sorcery?

497
00:30:24,270 --> 00:30:31,387
Since I’m from the Marandiyya clan, and our ancestors were known for religion and for using drums

498
00:30:32,333 --> 00:30:38,604
He said, Do you still make amulet spells and play the drums?

499
00:30:38,870 --> 00:30:41,213
And I knew him. I knew him well

500
00:30:42,495 --> 00:30:43,901
I told him, I swear, Sheikh

501
00:30:44,784 --> 00:30:48,705
I told him these words when you stop playing the <i>rababa</i> [string instrument]

502
00:30:49,487 --> 00:30:52,924
He said to me, Are you the brother of Abdul Rahim Shuweimi?

503
00:30:53,370 --> 00:30:54,705
I said, Yes, I’m his brother

504
00:30:55,143 --> 00:30:56,604
I said, But, Sheikh

505
00:30:57,854 --> 00:30:59,319
At that time, my family was trying to use mediations for me

506
00:30:59,344 --> 00:31:05,032
My mother, an old woman, wherever she saw a clan sheikh or a member of ISIS

507
00:31:05,057 --> 00:31:10,114
Any man with a long beard, she would go to him and say, My son has children, and so on

508
00:31:10,901 --> 00:31:13,432
She would follow them around for her son, hoping they’d release me, and I had children

509
00:31:13,456 --> 00:31:17,168
My children became my parents’ responsibility, and they had no power to help

510
00:31:18,809 --> 00:31:21,595
We argued about this topic

511
00:31:21,924 --> 00:31:23,680
Then he said to me, You’re a filthy person

512
00:31:23,705 --> 00:31:27,537
I said, So now for you the Muslim is filthy, and Muslims deserve execution

513
00:31:28,065 --> 00:31:30,698
It’s the rule of the strong over the weak, and there’s no power or strength

514
00:31:31,627 --> 00:31:34,259
He said to me, God willing, you won’t leave this place

515
00:31:34,884 --> 00:31:37,056
He brought in a man, and that man

516
00:31:38,337 --> 00:31:40,735
Had a medium-sized passenger van

517
00:31:41,556 --> 00:31:45,009
His house was in the Kalta area in Raqqa’s countryside, and he used to transport female teachers

518
00:31:45,634 --> 00:31:51,706
The group forced teachers to attend repentance courses. The point is, he used to drive those teachers

519
00:31:52,251 --> 00:31:55,939
The group accused him of smuggling people out of Raqqa

520
00:31:56,532 --> 00:31:58,414
They brought the man and blindfolded him

521
00:31:59,821 --> 00:32:01,712
That act was meant as punishment for me

522
00:32:02,134 --> 00:32:04,910
I felt it was a punishment for me, and while he was talking to me

523
00:32:05,501 --> 00:32:06,782
He made me sit on a chair

524
00:32:07,665 --> 00:32:08,798
While I was blindfolded

525
00:32:10,243 --> 00:32:16,384
I was only blindfolded and tied with plastic ties

526
00:32:16,409 --> 00:32:18,618
The kind used for bundling electric cables

527
00:32:20,525 --> 00:32:26,509
Then he brought the man and started beating him with a water hose called “Lakhdar Brahimi”

528
00:32:26,697 --> 00:32:28,485
He disfigured the man’s body with the beating

529
00:32:28,510 --> 00:32:30,190
The man cried intensely

530
00:32:31,018 --> 00:32:36,402
I could hear the hose striking near me, and he kept beating him until he killed him

531
00:32:37,105 --> 00:32:40,894
Finally, I was so upset that I said, He’ll kill this man if he continues

532
00:32:41,579 --> 00:32:46,407
I told him, I don’t want the interrogation anymore, just stop hitting him, because I realized he was doing it for my sake

533
00:32:46,699 --> 00:32:49,634
He couldn’t hit me, not out of fear

534
00:32:50,116 --> 00:32:53,164
But because there was no proof against me, so he had no right to beat me

535
00:32:53,189 --> 00:32:57,290
And because Abu Yousuf the interrogator and Abu Suhaib the Tunisian were above him in rank

536
00:32:57,315 --> 00:33:02,415
Although Abu Suhaib the Tunisian was very strict religiously, he never allowed anyone to be beaten

537
00:33:02,922 --> 00:33:05,211
He wouldn’t allow it, and that’s the truth

538
00:33:05,689 --> 00:33:10,289
He’s gone now, but may God reward him; that Tunisian man never allowed anyone to be beaten

539
00:33:12,852 --> 00:33:16,971
He disfigured the man. In the end, I told him, Don’t beat him to scare me, I don’t want the interrogation

540
00:33:16,996 --> 00:33:19,805
From now on, I won’t say I want interrogation or a judge

541
00:33:20,019 --> 00:33:21,388
Just leave the man alone

542
00:33:22,735 --> 00:33:25,094
I felt guilty, that I was the reason he was beaten

543
00:33:25,119 --> 00:33:28,656
Then Abu Yousuf came in to us

544
00:33:28,665 --> 00:33:31,147
He pulled me back into the group cell and said, Next time someone asks you

545
00:33:31,172 --> 00:33:33,430
Tell him you were interrogated and brought before the judge

546
00:33:33,438 --> 00:33:35,297
I said, Thank you, brother, may God guide you

547
00:33:36,555 --> 00:33:39,722
They took me into the cell, and they brought the man into my room

548
00:33:40,250 --> 00:33:41,805
In the first room, of course

549
00:33:42,877 --> 00:33:43,877
And I sat down

550
00:33:45,315 --> 00:33:47,531
When I saw the man, by God Almighty

551
00:33:47,790 --> 00:33:49,470
One of the hose strikes

552
00:33:49,993 --> 00:33:51,727
When he was suspended like this

553
00:33:52,188 --> 00:33:54,227
With an iron rod

554
00:33:54,586 --> 00:33:58,734
A thick iron rod, and his toes barely touched the ground

555
00:33:59,008 --> 00:34:04,008
The poor man was terrified; when they hit his chest, he lowered his head

556
00:34:04,119 --> 00:34:06,049
Then one of the hose strikes hit his face

557
00:34:06,665 --> 00:34:10,509
His face swelled painfully, and his eyes were no longer visible

558
00:34:11,204 --> 00:34:12,947
I truly felt

559
00:34:14,807 --> 00:34:16,461
That I carried that man’s guilt

560
00:34:16,486 --> 00:34:20,010
That same day, they brought a man from the al-Shanani family, a licorice drink seller

561
00:34:22,603 --> 00:34:24,931
Interviewer: Can you tell us their names if you know them?

562
00:34:25,463 --> 00:34:31,319
That man was from the Kalta area, but honestly, I don’t know his exact name

563
00:34:31,426 --> 00:34:36,118
But he was known as Abu Ahmad, and he drove a light-brown passenger car

564
00:34:36,478 --> 00:34:38,321
He still owns that car today

565
00:34:38,478 --> 00:34:40,078
But the man called al-Shanani

566
00:34:40,103 --> 00:34:43,804
His name was probably Mustafa al-Shanani, also called Abu Firas al-Shanani, a well-known man

567
00:34:43,829 --> 00:34:45,320
At the intersection of the Sayf al-Dawla area

568
00:34:45,696 --> 00:34:52,391
With February 23 Street in Raqqa city. They’ve been selling licorice for generations, known as the Shanani family

569
00:34:52,477 --> 00:34:53,696
They brought the old man

570
00:34:54,308 --> 00:34:58,917
When they brought him into Point 11, the old man had no skin left on his back

571
00:34:59,181 --> 00:35:00,187
Only bone remained

572
00:35:00,212 --> 00:35:03,235
I spent more than 25 days treating the old man

573
00:35:03,260 --> 00:35:05,118
And to this day, he and I are friends

574
00:35:05,485 --> 00:35:07,393
He tells me, How can I repay you?

575
00:35:07,418 --> 00:35:13,489
And I say I did nothing. I just helped treat him, using the group’s medicines since he was elderly

576
00:35:13,610 --> 00:35:17,614
At that time, they detained him and his son, whose name was Firas

577
00:35:18,403 --> 00:35:19,915
He was in the second group cell

578
00:35:20,243 --> 00:35:21,681
And they broke his leg

579
00:35:22,095 --> 00:35:24,598
Firas is still alive

580
00:35:25,056 --> 00:35:27,399
Those who conducted the interrogations with us

581
00:35:28,556 --> 00:35:30,321
Were from inside the prison

582
00:35:30,446 --> 00:35:33,526
Like Abu Yousuf the interrogator and Abu Abdul Rahman

583
00:35:33,712 --> 00:35:35,595
The second one was from the al-Sahou clan

584
00:35:36,089 --> 00:35:40,401
The group deliberately used people in interrogations who had strong intelligence connections inside the city

585
00:35:41,665 --> 00:35:44,399
That’s one point, and the first and most important

586
00:35:44,892 --> 00:35:46,634
The most important and strongest thing they had

587
00:35:47,337 --> 00:35:49,603
Was that they had security agents inside the prison

588
00:35:50,009 --> 00:35:53,251
They had security agents from our own people, from our towns, sadly

589
00:35:53,321 --> 00:35:56,790
ISIS had security agents from our local people working inside the prison for money

590
00:35:57,274 --> 00:36:01,306
For example, someone would come, and I’d look at him, and one of them

591
00:36:01,860 --> 00:36:04,017
Was from the al-Bou Saraya clan, named Abdullah

592
00:36:04,259 --> 00:36:07,204
He sat beside me, and I had been in prison for 10 days

593
00:36:09,478 --> 00:36:15,501
When he sat and started crying, saying he was wronged and jailed over selling a pistol

594
00:36:15,563 --> 00:36:18,892
I trusted him, as I had nothing to hide

595
00:36:19,368 --> 00:36:22,712
The group’s informants or security men

596
00:36:22,938 --> 00:36:28,310
Would come acting like victims, saying they were innocent, and talk about ISIS in front of me, saying we’ll get out tomorrow

597
00:36:28,415 --> 00:36:31,732
And say, God is generous, and promise that such-and-such faction would enter the city

598
00:36:31,845 --> 00:36:35,001
So the person in front of them would confess and start talking

599
00:36:35,079 --> 00:36:40,306
These were the ones ISIS sent in as informants and internal agents

600
00:36:40,412 --> 00:36:42,217
They were very intelligent people

601
00:36:42,795 --> 00:36:46,193
One of these people was named Abdullah al-Asaad

602
00:36:46,508 --> 00:36:50,407
His house was next to the Nabhan Glass Shop in Raqqa, and he was killed

603
00:36:51,889 --> 00:36:55,029
While fighting in one of the battles

604
00:36:55,392 --> 00:36:58,717
He started crying in front of me, and about 40 days later

605
00:36:59,115 --> 00:37:01,904
He started crying again and told me that his mother had died

606
00:37:02,946 --> 00:37:06,912
When I got out of prison, his goal was to get information from me

607
00:37:07,376 --> 00:37:10,986
When I was released, I went to his house to offer condolences to his father

608
00:37:11,011 --> 00:37:14,193
And I said, Keep your faith strong, Abdullah is crying and mourning his mother

609
00:37:14,218 --> 00:37:17,767
Since I had been released, it was my duty to visit my friend’s family who was still in prison

610
00:37:17,792 --> 00:37:22,826
I was shocked when his mother came out, cursing him and saying, May God never grant him success, and that she had disowned him

611
00:37:23,058 --> 00:37:25,602
She said, He claims I’m dead, but he’s an informant for the group

612
00:37:26,811 --> 00:37:30,939
There were many people who infiltrated others in this same way

613
00:37:31,894 --> 00:37:34,011
Our people are kind-hearted and simple

614
00:37:34,487 --> 00:37:38,004
So they might slip and say something by mistake, and that security informant

615
00:37:38,581 --> 00:37:39,581
Would then

616
00:37:40,042 --> 00:37:45,097
Report it to the security forces, and based on that, the person would be accused. Many people were killed that way

617
00:37:46,175 --> 00:37:48,011
Stories like this were common

618
00:37:52,114 --> 00:37:54,332
As for torture methods

619
00:37:55,324 --> 00:37:56,324
Torture

620
00:37:57,668 --> 00:37:59,928
We witnessed how they tortured people

621
00:38:00,926 --> 00:38:02,404
The problem was that they had two styles

622
00:38:02,847 --> 00:38:04,420
One underground

623
00:38:04,637 --> 00:38:06,412
And another above ground, completely different

624
00:38:07,301 --> 00:38:12,215
Like a person with two faces—and both faces were terrifying

625
00:38:12,761 --> 00:38:15,006
As for the Hisba (religious police)

626
00:38:16,125 --> 00:38:17,624
It had 20 faces

627
00:38:17,771 --> 00:38:19,477
Regarding torture methods

628
00:38:19,998 --> 00:38:25,013
Anything you can imagine existed. Many locals were imprisoned

629
00:38:25,560 --> 00:38:30,326
And subjected to different torture methods—for example, crucifixion

630
00:38:31,305 --> 00:38:34,959
Or they’d shackle your hands like this with cuffs

631
00:38:35,388 --> 00:38:39,615
When your hands were raised with the cuffs, your ribs would tear apart from here

632
00:38:39,943 --> 00:38:43,795
When Abu Seif lifted the prisoner—he was a huge man from eating too much Western food

633
00:38:44,003 --> 00:38:47,050
God gave him the strength to eat 4 or 5 sandwiches

634
00:38:47,246 --> 00:38:49,386
At the expense of the so-called caliphate

635
00:38:49,605 --> 00:38:52,043
He was very strong, while I was weak

636
00:38:52,379 --> 00:38:57,456
He would grab me by the neck and lift me about 20 or 30 centimeters off the ground

637
00:38:57,481 --> 00:39:00,465
My legs would kick violently, just like in American movies

638
00:39:00,871 --> 00:39:05,019
I couldn’t walk or breathe from the pain in my chest

639
00:39:05,457 --> 00:39:11,096
I had tonsillitis, my ribs were broken, and to this day I still suffer chest pain

640
00:39:11,347 --> 00:39:13,020
At that time

641
00:39:13,457 --> 00:39:18,988
The guys, God bless them, took care of me for about 68 days

642
00:39:19,430 --> 00:39:25,055
They would take me to the toilets, bathe me, and cared for me well

643
00:39:25,119 --> 00:39:29,923
Among them were Ibrahim Abu Nashwa and Ibrahim Ayyoub, known as Shantar

644
00:39:30,342 --> 00:39:34,529
All the guys who were with me in prison were kind and helped me in every way

645
00:39:34,730 --> 00:39:40,666
I was never cared for in my life the way those six men cared for me when I was the seventh

646
00:39:40,691 --> 00:39:43,404
When I was broken and my ribs were shattered in prison

647
00:39:47,662 --> 00:39:49,182
Out of fear and terror

648
00:39:49,660 --> 00:39:53,115
My ribs and legs could barely move

649
00:39:53,496 --> 00:39:58,972
In the room above us there were solitary cells, each about one square meter, with a ceiling

650
00:39:59,465 --> 00:40:01,715
Barriwi carried me and we went up

651
00:40:02,425 --> 00:40:06,222
He broke a small iron piece from one of the solitary cells

652
00:40:09,183 --> 00:40:12,158
Then Barriwi started scraping the wall

653
00:40:12,183 --> 00:40:14,433
The wall was coated with smooth cement

654
00:40:14,458 --> 00:40:18,121
We discovered it was made of modern white stone, not black stone

655
00:40:19,496 --> 00:40:23,715
Barriwi said, “Talal al-Shuweimi, let’s escape,” so we tried to run away

656
00:40:24,399 --> 00:40:25,813
It was me and Barriwi

657
00:40:26,230 --> 00:40:33,636
And Ibrahim Ayyoub, known as Shantar, was watching the door with Bara al-Ano

658
00:40:35,400 --> 00:40:40,918
We started digging the wall and dug the length of about two bricks and the width of two more

659
00:40:41,697 --> 00:40:45,800
But we were terrified, because each brick

660
00:40:46,566 --> 00:40:49,097
Had two sides, one of them thick

661
00:40:49,871 --> 00:40:55,877
The thick side was pressed against another thick side, with a cement layer in between that couldn’t be broken easily—it made a loud sound

662
00:40:55,902 --> 00:41:01,683
Across from our room, one of the group’s members was standing guard

663
00:41:03,159 --> 00:41:04,286
We were terrified

664
00:41:04,753 --> 00:41:09,511
I went to the sheikh and told him, Out of fear, no one knows what to do—especially the sentenced ones

665
00:41:09,903 --> 00:41:11,722
So I said to the imprisoned sheikh with us

666
00:41:12,160 --> 00:41:13,325
My brother

667
00:41:14,410 --> 00:41:20,105
Read to us from the Quran, maybe God will save us from them and help us escape

668
00:41:20,528 --> 00:41:25,902
Or make them blind to us—things like that, which are close to sorcery, God forbid

669
00:41:25,962 --> 00:41:29,830
But we were desperate, and a drowning man clings to a straw

670
00:41:30,376 --> 00:41:35,526
As you know, I was sentenced to execution, and a drowning man clings not just to a straw but to the water itself

671
00:41:36,111 --> 00:41:37,517
Trying to hold onto the water

672
00:41:38,392 --> 00:41:41,125
The sheikh actually believed himself

673
00:41:41,150 --> 00:41:44,344
He was a man whose house was on Mansour Street in Raqqa, sentenced to execution

674
00:41:44,369 --> 00:41:46,119
On charges of sorcery

675
00:41:46,923 --> 00:41:49,830
He said he treated people with traditional Arabic medicine

676
00:41:50,486 --> 00:41:53,509
He went to treat a woman who had joint pain in her legs

677
00:41:53,798 --> 00:41:56,511
And they arrested him for that, accusing him of witchcraft

678
00:41:56,964 --> 00:41:58,602
That man started reciting

679
00:41:59,620 --> 00:42:05,003
And it became like some satanic ritual, while we continued pounding on the wall

680
00:42:05,573 --> 00:42:08,917
Hard, but the guard outside didn’t hear us

681
00:42:09,581 --> 00:42:14,589
The guard sitting outside was an ISIS member who had just finished his training course

682
00:42:15,066 --> 00:42:16,323
His name was Abu al-Yaman

683
00:42:16,730 --> 00:42:19,011
Abu al-Yaman was from Aleppo Province

684
00:42:21,566 --> 00:42:25,417
When we made an opening in the wall, one of us, a diabetic man

685
00:42:25,442 --> 00:42:28,206
Named Ibrahim al-Ali al-Alkan, known as Abu Nashwa

686
00:42:28,620 --> 00:42:31,518
Got so scared that his blood sugar spiked

687
00:42:32,433 --> 00:42:33,730
He almost died

688
00:42:34,699 --> 00:42:35,925
And he actually did die

689
00:42:36,612 --> 00:42:38,901
They had brought us wool blankets

690
00:42:39,894 --> 00:42:42,800
Because winter was approaching

691
00:42:43,558 --> 00:42:47,948
We tore up those wool blankets, and also some other covers

692
00:42:48,276 --> 00:42:52,198
When we broke through the wall of the Hisba prison, behind it was an investigation building on Sajiyah Street

693
00:42:52,737 --> 00:42:55,940
There was a depth of about 7 meters

694
00:42:56,214 --> 00:42:58,698
After 7 meters, there was the yard of a ground-floor house

695
00:42:59,847 --> 00:43:02,659
Because of the pounding noise, the homeowner came out

696
00:43:02,894 --> 00:43:07,394
He shouted, Who are you? I said, Uncle, I’m Talal al-Shuweimi, your relative

697
00:43:07,511 --> 00:43:11,901
And Ibrahim al-Fakkash said, I’m from the Fakkash family, from the Shibli Salamah clan

698
00:43:12,026 --> 00:43:16,925
We started crying and begged him not to report us—we were sentenced to execution

699
00:43:17,245 --> 00:43:19,417
The man cried along with us

700
00:43:19,987 --> 00:43:23,839
He started crying and said, My nephews, jump down quickly

701
00:43:24,566 --> 00:43:26,878
So they wouldn’t cut off my neck with yours

702
00:43:28,605 --> 00:43:30,816
And the man was holding a laser lighter for us

703
00:43:31,058 --> 00:43:35,397
He looked at us and said, “My brothers’ sons, hurry up, the daylight has broken,” and when we finished

704
00:43:36,620 --> 00:43:39,201
Ibrahim al-Alkan fell ill

705
00:43:39,683 --> 00:43:41,019
And the last time we went out

706
00:43:41,386 --> 00:43:44,839
The house of Emir Abu Seif was on Sajiyah Street

707
00:43:45,917 --> 00:43:49,593
The Hisba (religious police) base was on Sajiyah Street, and the road was like this

708
00:43:49,797 --> 00:43:53,312
Sajiyah Street is on the southern side

709
00:43:53,526 --> 00:43:56,921
The Hisba is on the northern side, and Abu Seif’s house is on Sajiyah Street

710
00:43:56,980 --> 00:43:59,501
The organization had taken that house from a Kurdish family

711
00:43:59,526 --> 00:44:05,679
The owner was called Abu Sateef, a well-known bicycle repairman in Raqqa and on Sajiyah Street

712
00:44:05,773 --> 00:44:07,507
So Abu Seif took his house

713
00:44:08,128 --> 00:44:12,906
Abu Seif, the Emir of the Investigation, took the house of Abu Sateef, the Kurdish bicycle repairman

714
00:44:13,305 --> 00:44:15,932
The Hisba base was across from his house, and when he went out

715
00:44:18,245 --> 00:44:22,706
He saw that the wall had been destroyed across the width of about two and a half rooms

716
00:44:23,476 --> 00:44:27,800
Suddenly, the security men surrounded the area and came up to us

717
00:44:29,008 --> 00:44:35,198
They started shooting at my feet and separated me from the other young men

718
00:44:35,565 --> 00:44:37,104
Then they brought us back again

719
00:44:37,659 --> 00:44:42,425
For the case of crucifixion and suspension, and of course the beatings and insults

720
00:44:46,823 --> 00:44:49,526
I was tortured and kept being tortured for 3 more days

721
00:44:50,550 --> 00:44:53,807
After 3 days, they took me to the court

722
00:44:56,393 --> 00:45:02,495
There was an air fan in the room where they put us

723
00:45:02,706 --> 00:45:05,908
It was installed in the wall for air and odor ventilation, called the <i>sharaq</i> [door vent]

724
00:45:06,893 --> 00:45:08,425
I told the guys, “Listen, guys

725
00:45:10,979 --> 00:45:13,026
If they take us down to the same room

726
00:45:13,393 --> 00:45:16,041
The <i>sharaq</i> switch is below, and we’re placed upstairs in the solitary cells

727
00:45:16,066 --> 00:45:18,620
When you turn on the metal <i>sharaq</i>, it will make noise

728
00:45:19,050 --> 00:45:24,721
Whoever among you goes down to our old room, turn it on so we know who was sent there”

729
00:45:25,909 --> 00:45:27,706
The first one they summoned was al-Bariwi

730
00:45:29,237 --> 00:45:33,522
We waited 5 minutes, 15 minutes, half an hour, and the <i>sharaq</i> still didn’t turn on

731
00:45:35,182 --> 00:45:39,229
Then they summoned another person too

732
00:45:40,050 --> 00:45:41,800
And the <i>sharaq</i> still didn’t turn on

733
00:45:43,108 --> 00:45:45,706
Fear and terror spread among us

734
00:45:46,917 --> 00:45:48,026
Then they called my name, Talal al-Shuweimi

735
00:45:48,051 --> 00:45:52,518
They shackled me and blindfolded me. Abu Seif lifted me by my shoulder and led me

736
00:45:53,424 --> 00:45:55,456
And Abu Hudhayfa held me by the other shoulder

737
00:45:57,284 --> 00:46:04,190
They carried me forcefully as if they were about to carry out the sentence against me and took me out

738
00:46:06,026 --> 00:46:07,673
They said, “Stand,” so I stood

739
00:46:08,573 --> 00:46:12,024
He asked me, “Are you so-and-so?” I said, “Yes, I am”

740
00:46:13,148 --> 00:46:18,206
He said, “You did this and that.” I said, “Yes, Sheikh, I was the biggest cigarette trader

741
00:46:18,698 --> 00:46:22,923
Under the caliphate, but God guided me, and I quit over a year or a year and a half ago”

742
00:46:22,948 --> 00:46:27,011
“And now, after I quit the trade, you summon me and treat me like this?”

743
00:46:27,948 --> 00:46:30,701
We argued, and the sheikh started insulting me

744
00:46:31,268 --> 00:46:36,995
He said, “You’re talkative and loud. You think religion is a game,” and so on

745
00:46:37,378 --> 00:46:41,518
He said, “You and that woman—I won’t mention her name—

746
00:46:41,979 --> 00:46:44,763
You both smoke hookah and walk around with that other woman”

747
00:46:44,788 --> 00:46:47,496
They were all women suffering from poverty and hunger

748
00:46:48,013 --> 00:46:51,588
They traded cigarettes to earn a living and support their children

749
00:46:51,613 --> 00:46:55,765
Some were widows, others had children, and one had a disabled child

750
00:46:55,796 --> 00:46:58,972
They relied on God and borrowed cigarettes from me

751
00:46:58,997 --> 00:47:03,097
To sell them, cover their expenses, and provide for their families

752
00:47:04,488 --> 00:47:05,589
So I said to him, “Sheikh

753
00:47:06,644 --> 00:47:10,253
You’re accusing me of false charges

754
00:47:10,613 --> 00:47:14,550
Keep the cigarette charge; it’s better than accusing me of adultery

755
00:47:15,253 --> 00:47:19,900
Imagine, I entered prison for cigarette trading and ended up with 10 other charges I had nothing to do with

756
00:47:19,925 --> 00:47:23,019
And sadly, I didn’t even know about them until the very end

757
00:47:23,261 --> 00:47:27,988
In the end, I learned that the cases I was sentenced for had nothing to do with cigarettes

758
00:47:28,144 --> 00:47:30,823
My arrest and interrogation were indeed for cigarette trading

759
00:47:31,244 --> 00:47:34,561
But eventually, none of the charges were related to that

760
00:47:34,586 --> 00:47:37,206
Even in the same court, they accused me of adultery

761
00:47:37,933 --> 00:47:41,042
With one of the women who sold cigarettes

762
00:47:41,067 --> 00:47:48,826
Now tell me, does it make sense? I have 3 wives, my daughters are unmarried, and I have 13 children

763
00:47:49,339 --> 00:47:50,698
And now I’m going to commit adultery?

764
00:47:51,370 --> 00:47:54,738
After 3 wives and after reaching 40 or 45 years old?

765
00:47:54,972 --> 00:47:56,798
I told him, “Sheikh, that’s not logical

766
00:47:57,014 --> 00:47:59,896
Leave me with the cigarette trading charge, may God guide you

767
00:48:00,107 --> 00:48:02,902
Judge me for that—it’s better than judging me for adultery”

768
00:48:04,238 --> 00:48:07,529
I told him, “If you don’t fear God, then you should be feared.” He said, “Do you think we don’t fear God?”

769
00:48:07,620 --> 00:48:10,795
Then he stood up and hit me. I don’t know with what, because I was blindfolded

770
00:48:10,855 --> 00:48:15,441
I felt something running down my head, like heat

771
00:48:17,964 --> 00:48:20,800
And that’s when he pronounced the sentence

772
00:48:21,534 --> 00:48:28,482
He didn’t give me anything, didn’t even let me sit. He just asked me a few harsh questions

773
00:48:28,608 --> 00:48:30,894
Then said, “We sentence you to <i>qisas</i> [retribution]

774
00:48:32,159 --> 00:48:33,314
You did such and such”

775
00:48:33,339 --> 00:48:35,003
He asked, “What do you think of my sentence?”

776
00:48:35,363 --> 00:48:38,109
At that moment, I mocked the judgment

777
00:48:38,636 --> 00:48:42,719
I didn’t take it seriously. I was just a cigarette trader—what does <i>qisas</i> have to do with that?

778
00:48:43,305 --> 00:48:46,503
Why should I be sentenced to retribution for cigarette trading?

779
00:48:47,777 --> 00:48:51,105
They judged me as a corrupter on earth

780
00:48:51,902 --> 00:48:54,496
But “corruption on earth” means armed robbery and banditry

781
00:48:55,300 --> 00:48:57,816
Armed assault—not cigarette trading

782
00:48:59,339 --> 00:49:02,198
And today, the whole world smokes cigarettes

783
00:49:03,089 --> 00:49:04,995
Everyone smokes cigarettes

784
00:49:06,128 --> 00:49:08,316
Even alcohol existed in the time of the Companions

785
00:49:08,605 --> 00:49:11,167
But now, in the time of these “new Companions,”

786
00:49:11,792 --> 00:49:14,105
They want to cut off heads and hands

787
00:49:14,792 --> 00:49:18,589
But there’s no power or strength left—today, they’re strong and we’re weak

788
00:49:19,839 --> 00:49:21,206
He asked me, “What do you say about the judgment?”

789
00:49:21,498 --> 00:49:24,318
I said, “Me?”—I wasn’t afraid, I was relaxed

790
00:49:25,042 --> 00:49:27,550
I wasn’t scared at all; I was at ease

791
00:49:28,238 --> 00:49:33,222
I told him, “I’m satisfied with your judgment.” When I said that, they were surprised

792
00:49:33,816 --> 00:49:38,206
He said, “Why are you satisfied?” I said, “Isn’t this God’s decree, the Almighty?”

793
00:49:38,602 --> 00:49:42,113
“You’re ruling by God’s <i>sharia</i>, and I’m content with God’s law”

794
00:49:42,738 --> 00:49:43,800
Then he said to me

795
00:49:44,519 --> 00:49:46,214
“What will you say to the seven-member committee?”

796
00:49:46,488 --> 00:49:51,406
I said, “Who are the seven-member committee?” He said, “They’re the sheikhs, because your file will be sent to them”

797
00:49:52,839 --> 00:49:55,222
I said, “What difference will my words make?”

798
00:49:55,247 --> 00:49:59,831
“You already sentenced me to <i>qisas</i>—what can those sheikhs do now?”

799
00:50:01,292 --> 00:50:04,519
He said, “Say whatever you want to tell them”

800
00:50:04,545 --> 00:50:09,628
I said, “Send them my regards and tell them the Sheikh’s judgment is false upon falsehood”

801
00:50:12,105 --> 00:50:13,795
Your entire verdict is invalid upon invalid

802
00:50:14,318 --> 00:50:17,599
My case is about cigarettes, and you accused me of adultery and other charges

803
00:50:17,831 --> 00:50:19,603
Just to sentence me to execution

804
00:50:19,628 --> 00:50:25,201
How can you sentence me to execution while I’m blindfolded, shackled, and standing on my feet?

805
00:50:25,847 --> 00:50:27,027
Then one of them stood up

806
00:50:28,120 --> 00:50:29,120
And hit me

807
00:50:30,159 --> 00:50:34,556
He punched me in the stomach and I fell to the ground. They held me as another came from behind and hit me

808
00:50:34,581 --> 00:50:37,204
Of course, I was blindfolded and didn’t know where the blows were coming from

809
00:50:38,081 --> 00:50:42,909
When he hit me, I said, I accept the judgment and law of God Almighty

810
00:50:44,503 --> 00:50:45,899
Then they brought me down

811
00:50:46,603 --> 00:50:49,448
And all I was thinking about during that conversation

812
00:50:50,339 --> 00:50:55,628
When they brought me down, I was wondering where I would go. My friends hadn’t opened the <i>sharaqa</i> [door vent] inside the room

813
00:50:56,300 --> 00:51:00,628
I was surprised when I came down the stairs because I knew the way down to the investigation area

814
00:51:01,182 --> 00:51:05,847
We went straight down, then came to a small landing, turned, and went down again

815
00:51:06,456 --> 00:51:10,509
Right in front of us was the investigation door, leading westward

816
00:51:10,534 --> 00:51:15,119
Suddenly, they took me toward the investigation door, and then

817
00:51:15,870 --> 00:51:17,597
They unlocked the cuffs on my hands

818
00:51:18,323 --> 00:51:21,417
And started shackling my left hand

819
00:51:21,956 --> 00:51:25,526
When they shackled my left hand, I lifted the cloth blindfold from my eyes

820
00:51:25,972 --> 00:51:29,175
I looked and saw that everyone was masked, and at the investigation door

821
00:51:29,323 --> 00:51:33,030
There was a black vehicle for transporting prisoners, marked “Judicial Police”

822
00:51:33,104 --> 00:51:36,589
When they issued execution sentences

823
00:51:37,081 --> 00:51:44,311
They handed the sentenced prisoners to the Judicial Police, which handled executions and amputations

824
00:51:44,917 --> 00:51:46,323
At that moment

825
00:51:46,831 --> 00:51:50,834
Terror, death, and pain fell upon me

826
00:51:50,952 --> 00:51:55,175
It was a situation no one would envy, terrible to the point that

827
00:51:55,191 --> 00:52:01,853
It truly defies description, no matter how I try to explain it

828
00:52:01,885 --> 00:52:07,157
When I saw the Judicial Police and their black vehicle parked there

829
00:52:07,782 --> 00:52:10,782
I saw my friend, Ibrahim al-Fakkash

830
00:52:12,251 --> 00:52:13,909
And another man, both shackled

831
00:52:15,252 --> 00:52:16,509
They hit me immediately

832
00:52:16,774 --> 00:52:20,852
Blindfolded me again, put a black bag over my head, shackled me, and made me sit down

833
00:52:22,626 --> 00:52:28,790
I felt that Ibrahim al-Fakkash, out of fear, was repeating, “There is no god but God”

834
00:52:28,819 --> 00:52:31,714
I crawled toward him

835
00:52:33,204 --> 00:52:35,104
And it was sunset time

836
00:52:36,206 --> 00:52:37,804
I asked him, Are you al-Breiwi?

837
00:52:38,300 --> 00:52:40,089
He said, Yes. I asked, What did they do?

838
00:52:40,272 --> 00:52:41,796
He said, They sentenced me to execution

839
00:52:43,499 --> 00:52:46,858
Then we cried—not because we wanted to, but out of sheer terror

840
00:52:47,202 --> 00:52:51,397
Our fear wasn’t only of death or being shot

841
00:52:51,741 --> 00:52:58,483
But from imagining them holding our heads and slitting our throats with a knife—that’s what truly terrified us

842
00:52:58,530 --> 00:53:03,515
Every second we were dying millions of times inside

843
00:53:04,327 --> 00:53:10,991
Or a billion times—each time imagining the knife descending on our necks

844
00:53:11,108 --> 00:53:15,294
We had already seen ISIS videos showing people being slaughtered with knives

845
00:53:15,319 --> 00:53:22,569
Those scenes stuck in my mind, and I imagined the blade cutting through my neck

846
00:53:23,163 --> 00:53:24,614
We cried from fear

847
00:53:24,639 --> 00:53:29,343
We knew well who ISIS were—they had no mercy, no compassion

848
00:53:30,788 --> 00:53:34,382
The third, the fourth, and others came, but one person remained

849
00:53:35,716 --> 00:53:38,115
It was during Ramadan, and we were fasting

850
00:53:41,014 --> 00:53:44,413
As you know, at sunset, when the call to prayer begins for those fasting

851
00:53:47,755 --> 00:53:49,911
Ibrahim al-Alkan said, I want water

852
00:53:49,935 --> 00:53:54,630
Before you cut off our heads, we ask you to bring us water—we are fasting

853
00:53:59,841 --> 00:54:01,161
So they brought us water

854
00:54:01,841 --> 00:54:03,990
We couldn’t see, because we were blindfolded

855
00:54:04,490 --> 00:54:06,317
They gave the water to Ibrahim

856
00:54:07,395 --> 00:54:12,294
When he drank, the water got stuck in his throat from fear

857
00:54:12,958 --> 00:54:17,129
It lodged in his throat, and he began choking

858
00:54:17,723 --> 00:54:21,692
I was so terrified, I thought they were strangling us one by one

859
00:54:23,270 --> 00:54:27,206
At first, when we heard the sunset call to prayer, we relaxed, thinking no execution would happen then

860
00:54:27,231 --> 00:54:30,216
Because they usually wanted crowds to film their productions

861
00:54:30,716 --> 00:54:35,845
So when the call to prayer came, we felt some relief, knowing that executions never happened at sunset or night

862
00:54:36,434 --> 00:54:38,692
They never carried out executions at that time

863
00:54:40,372 --> 00:54:42,762
When Ibrahim started choking, fear overtook me

864
00:54:43,747 --> 00:54:48,958
I crawled backward and ended up in the arms of my friend al-Breiwi

865
00:54:49,012 --> 00:54:52,005
When I stretched out my right hand, I touched the shoe of one of the ISIS members

866
00:54:52,317 --> 00:54:54,770
Each of us had an ISIS member standing right beside him

867
00:54:56,204 --> 00:55:00,442
I jumped into al-Breiwi’s arms and told him, They’re going to strangle us one by one

868
00:55:01,864 --> 00:55:08,552
Then they brought the last person—I think it was Baraa al-Ano—and shackled him

869
00:55:10,637 --> 00:55:12,212
They put us inside the vehicle

870
00:55:12,755 --> 00:55:18,739
We could see a little from under the blindfold. Inside the vehicle were sharp metal pieces and swords

871
00:55:19,083 --> 00:55:23,381
It felt like we were in a scene from the “Khalid ibn al-Walid” series from the sword era

872
00:55:23,794 --> 00:55:25,200
We just sat there

873
00:55:26,512 --> 00:55:33,512
Since we were locals and knew the streets well from selling cigarettes there

874
00:55:33,614 --> 00:55:36,200
Sometimes we could tell where we were heading

875
00:55:36,645 --> 00:55:39,114
We reached the Euphrates Basin area roughly

876
00:55:40,900 --> 00:55:42,005
Then the road disappeared

877
00:55:43,184 --> 00:55:45,661
They pushed our heads down and spoke to us

878
00:55:47,114 --> 00:55:49,856
There were two escort vehicles alongside the one carrying us

879
00:55:50,966 --> 00:55:54,848
The main vehicle was black, designated for prisoner transport, marked “Judicial Police”

880
00:55:55,198 --> 00:56:00,996
Among the escorts was Abu Khaled al-Idlibi, the Emir of the Islamic Police

881
00:56:02,864 --> 00:56:05,755
They took us to the al-Jazra junction area in Raqqa city

882
00:56:06,403 --> 00:56:10,005
The next day, we learned that we were at the al-Jazra junction

883
00:56:11,606 --> 00:56:16,802
They put us in a small isolated room with only a toilet

884
00:56:17,993 --> 00:56:21,598
A small room with a toilet recently prepared and designated for us

885
00:56:22,348 --> 00:56:25,606
There was a small window in the wall like this

886
00:56:26,907 --> 00:56:29,770
It had thick iron bars

887
00:56:30,411 --> 00:56:35,091
They brought us new iron chains—thick ones, not thin

888
00:56:35,591 --> 00:56:39,169
As if they were meant to restrain some giant beast

889
00:56:39,194 --> 00:56:42,919
Like in American or foreign movies

890
00:56:43,278 --> 00:56:49,542
There was a huge gorilla in one movie that they enlarged with cameras and computers

891
00:56:49,567 --> 00:56:53,098
It felt like they were chaining a giant gorilla with those massive chains

892
00:56:53,591 --> 00:56:56,481
The chains were so thick that the prisoner couldn’t even move his hand

893
00:56:57,270 --> 00:57:02,201
They shackled us with those chains, and between each person there were 26 links

894
00:57:02,841 --> 00:57:04,606
The chains were white and new

895
00:57:05,404 --> 00:57:09,169
Abu Seif told me he had bought them especially for me, of the expensive kind

896
00:57:09,194 --> 00:57:11,169
He said he bought them exclusively from Qoutli Street

897
00:57:11,559 --> 00:57:13,605
They also brought 7 locks

898
00:57:13,630 --> 00:57:17,902
They placed the chain on my hand and locked it with a padlock

899
00:57:17,927 --> 00:57:23,052
Then left 26 links’ space, chained my friend’s hand, and locked it too

900
00:57:23,077 --> 00:57:26,122
They used to bring us a plate of oil and thyme

901
00:57:26,669 --> 00:57:29,106
They would come in wearing masks and bring us food

902
00:57:29,211 --> 00:57:32,450
I used to tell Al-Bariwi, our charge isn’t about the cigarette trade

903
00:57:32,475 --> 00:57:35,362
They chained us and sentenced us to execution

904
00:57:35,387 --> 00:57:39,823
And today this man comes in bringing us food while masked, and we’re bound with iron chains

905
00:57:39,848 --> 00:57:44,652
They even spoke to us through cameras and loudspeakers, telling us to move back

906
00:57:44,677 --> 00:57:51,544
So we’d retreat and hide in a corner of the room while they brought in a plate of oil and thyme

907
00:57:51,950 --> 00:57:57,028
We’d eat like that, and during the first 7 days, we didn’t eat anything until an emir came in

908
00:57:58,130 --> 00:58:00,536
He was from the Al-Dabba family, his name was Abu Saqr

909
00:58:01,661 --> 00:58:05,255
May God grant him wellness, guide him, and forgive him

910
00:58:05,966 --> 00:58:08,434
May God forgive him in this life and the next

911
00:58:08,856 --> 00:58:12,610
He came to us and started sitting with us every day for half an hour

912
00:58:13,130 --> 00:58:15,223
He would tell us prophetic hadiths

913
00:58:15,536 --> 00:58:17,708
May God bless him and guide him

914
00:58:18,442 --> 00:58:20,294
And protect him for his children, God willing

915
00:58:21,333 --> 00:58:27,786
He began forcing us to eat, like how one feeds a patient in intensive care

916
00:58:27,811 --> 00:58:31,762
He’d put a bite of bread in our mouths, forcing us to eat

917
00:58:31,841 --> 00:58:33,919
He started easing our suffering a little

918
00:58:34,934 --> 00:58:38,317
We stayed like this under Abu Saqr’s care

919
00:58:39,692 --> 00:58:41,958
For about three and a half months

920
00:58:43,731 --> 00:58:47,231
Around three and a half months, or about three months and 20 days

921
00:58:47,833 --> 00:58:51,701
When Abu Saqr’s shift ended, another would take over at night

922
00:58:51,958 --> 00:58:55,311
No one dealt with us except Abu Saqr and the plate of thyme

923
00:58:55,770 --> 00:58:56,916
I fell ill

924
00:58:57,503 --> 00:58:59,177
And the weather turned cold

925
00:59:00,333 --> 00:59:04,833
It’s honestly painful to talk about

926
00:59:05,341 --> 00:59:08,005
It wasn’t a human act

927
00:59:08,841 --> 00:59:13,325
Nor an Islamic one, not even something the Jews of Khaybar would do

928
00:59:13,606 --> 00:59:18,317
Because 7 of us sentenced to execution were chained with iron shackles

929
00:59:18,731 --> 00:59:21,262
And there were 27 links between each man

930
00:59:21,544 --> 00:59:23,574
When I needed to go to the toilets

931
00:59:23,599 --> 00:59:25,200
God is witness to what I say

932
00:59:25,536 --> 00:59:28,175
If I wanted to go to the toilets

933
00:59:28,208 --> 00:59:30,402
And I wanted to sit to relieve myself

934
00:59:30,427 --> 00:59:33,817
When I sat, my friend next to me had to bend toward me

935
00:59:34,802 --> 00:59:38,403
The third had to bend his body, and the fourth had to stand over me

936
00:59:38,692 --> 00:59:43,879
Meaning four of us stood in the toilet so one could relieve himself, may God honor you

937
00:59:44,497 --> 00:59:49,270
What kind of Islam is that? What <i>sharia</i> allows it?

938
00:59:49,661 --> 00:59:55,997
Seven Muslim men chained together, entering the toilets three or four at a time

939
00:59:56,419 --> 00:59:57,919
It was disgusting behavior

940
00:59:59,825 --> 01:00:02,317
And when one of us got sick

941
01:00:02,966 --> 01:00:06,692
Many of the young men got diarrhea, or someone needed to urinate, it was obvious

942
01:00:07,075 --> 01:00:12,012
We all had to wake up, because between me and the next man were 26 links, so all 7 of us had to get up

943
01:00:12,698 --> 01:00:16,903
Especially when one of us was sick with diarrhea

944
01:00:19,364 --> 01:00:25,012
We stayed like that for about three and a half months, or three months and 20 days

945
01:00:29,895 --> 01:00:32,708
Our daily routine among ourselves

946
01:00:32,855 --> 01:00:38,520
We had no real routine, only reading the Quran, crying, and supplicating

947
01:00:38,919 --> 01:00:41,825
Asking God to free us and the nation of Muhammad

948
01:00:42,286 --> 01:00:45,409
At night, we’d sit

949
01:00:45,528 --> 01:00:51,786
Reciting the Quran and praying Fajr until sunrise

950
01:00:52,309 --> 01:00:54,731
We’d fall asleep drowsy, still in our chains

951
01:00:55,122 --> 01:01:00,403
We barely slept half an hour or less before waking up in fear—some crying, some deep in thought

952
01:01:00,835 --> 01:01:03,882
Some would sit alone in the corner, imagining death

953
01:01:03,907 --> 01:01:08,833
When they were about to execute one or a group, the organization would film an ISIS video

954
01:01:09,153 --> 01:01:10,524
On a disc or flash drive

955
01:01:10,880 --> 01:01:14,506
Abu Seif brought us a flash drive back then, and we watched it

956
01:01:14,661 --> 01:01:19,503
It was like horror movies; we were sentenced to death, and he made us watch people being beheaded

957
01:01:19,528 --> 01:01:22,028
May God not grant him success in this world or the next

958
01:01:22,059 --> 01:01:25,777
He showed us footage of an execution slaughterhouse in Deir ez-Zor Province

959
01:01:25,802 --> 01:01:29,034
Where they executed 35 people hanging from sharp iron hooks

960
01:01:29,059 --> 01:01:36,239
One emir was carrying two men like this, wearing a short white robe—he was from Deir ez-Zor

961
01:01:36,506 --> 01:01:37,706
He carried two men like that

962
01:01:38,786 --> 01:01:41,388
He killed them and hung them on iron hooks

963
01:01:41,466 --> 01:01:43,208
Then Mustafa, known as Abu Seif

964
01:01:43,778 --> 01:01:47,809
Said to me, “Look, Talal al-Shuweimi, do you see the execution prep, Talal al-Shuweimi?”

965
01:01:48,598 --> 01:01:49,833
And I was under a death sentence

966
01:01:49,942 --> 01:01:57,380
Sometimes the hallucinations and fear cause sicknesses like diarrhea, chills, and psychological illness

967
01:01:57,630 --> 01:02:00,130
There was a man with us named Qadri al-Dabba

968
01:02:00,302 --> 01:02:02,966
Qadri al-Dabba started screaming in his sleep

969
01:02:04,395 --> 01:02:11,341
His eyes bulged, foam came out of his mouth—he became seriously ill, not normal at all

970
01:02:12,247 --> 01:02:16,362
Interviewer: Did the organization help him, or did they leave him to suffer?

971
01:02:16,387 --> 01:02:22,656
They didn’t give him anything; his fits would come every 4 or 5 hours

972
01:02:22,680 --> 01:02:24,919
One time, I fell sick myself

973
01:02:25,458 --> 01:02:29,028
I got chills and severe diarrhea inside the prison

974
01:02:29,567 --> 01:02:34,692
It knocked me to the ground, and I was near death

975
01:02:35,528 --> 01:02:37,387
By God’s power, I recovered

976
01:02:37,412 --> 01:02:41,731
My friends spoke to the ISIS members, but they didn’t give me injections or any help

977
01:02:41,756 --> 01:02:45,356
That happened during the days I was sentenced to death

978
01:02:45,606 --> 01:02:49,042
I don’t know if my illness came from fear or was a real sickness

979
01:02:49,067 --> 01:02:53,677
When I fell ill, there was a jailer under Abu Seif named Abu Abdul Malik

980
01:02:53,825 --> 01:02:56,239
He was from Tabqa, originally from Aleppo Province

981
01:02:57,216 --> 01:03:01,942
He watched us through the cameras; even Ibrahim al-Fakkash started crying over me

982
01:03:02,356 --> 01:03:08,208
And Ibrahim al-Alkan recited Quran over me, rubbing my body and weeping, thinking I was dying

983
01:03:10,489 --> 01:03:17,583
And Ibrahim al-Ayyoub, nicknamed Shantar, was a simple, impatient man

984
01:03:17,887 --> 01:03:21,583
He stood up, started smashing the door, shouting, “Talal al-Shuweimi is dead!”

985
01:03:21,950 --> 01:03:24,106
Abu Abdul Malik answered him

986
01:03:25,052 --> 01:03:26,317
And said, when he dies

987
01:03:26,817 --> 01:03:30,692
When he dies, let us know so we can take him out—that’s what Abu Abdul Malik said

988
01:03:31,411 --> 01:03:35,137
Praise be to God, Talal al-Shuweimi is still alive by God’s grace

989
01:03:35,162 --> 01:03:39,317
Abu Abdul Malik was later struck by an airstrike on his way to Tabqa

990
01:03:40,442 --> 01:03:43,481
May God have mercy on him—I recited Al-Fatiha for him

991
01:03:47,905 --> 01:03:49,997
There were mediations everywhere

992
01:03:50,326 --> 01:03:54,997
But not before God Almighty—there’s no mediation, and no bribery works

993
01:03:56,059 --> 01:04:01,895
When I was sentenced to death, neither my mother, my father, nor anyone could help me

994
01:04:01,920 --> 01:04:04,497
Only God Almighty can help you

995
01:04:05,419 --> 01:04:08,692
And your deeds help you in their eyes

996
01:04:08,803 --> 01:04:10,464
But they still had mediations

997
01:04:10,489 --> 01:04:13,778
One of my neighbors was detained

998
01:04:14,614 --> 01:04:19,825
His name was Qusai Ahmad al-Omara—he paid them 5,000 dollars and was released

999
01:04:20,101 --> 01:04:21,411
In the final days, for example

1000
01:04:22,427 --> 01:04:26,184
I was under the death sentence when the judicial committee arrived

1001
01:04:26,817 --> 01:04:28,294
They started bringing me my wife

1002
01:04:29,153 --> 01:04:31,115
Then they started bringing me my second wife

1003
01:04:31,262 --> 01:04:34,177
Of course, in exchange for money, whoever wanted the price of a motorcycle, I gave it to him

1004
01:04:34,202 --> 01:04:36,692
And whoever wanted diesel for his house, I gave it to him

1005
01:04:37,200 --> 01:04:43,044
There were many things I benefited from after my family found out that I was in prison

1006
01:04:43,692 --> 01:04:45,606
We started playing openly

1007
01:04:46,028 --> 01:04:48,411
When my family found out that I was in prison

1008
01:04:48,630 --> 01:04:50,239
My wives started

1009
01:04:50,607 --> 01:04:51,607
And even

1010
01:04:52,607 --> 01:04:57,075
Almost every day they came to visit me, one day they came, one day they didn’t

1011
01:04:57,286 --> 01:04:59,848
Of course secretly, so no one would see us outside

1012
01:04:59,873 --> 01:05:03,067
The prison was in a narrow corner facing my family’s house, and I saw them secretly

1013
01:05:03,092 --> 01:05:07,317
They brought silver and gold coins, and their food was now paid for by us personally

1014
01:05:07,950 --> 01:05:10,731
We were 7 people sentenced to execution

1015
01:05:11,247 --> 01:05:16,618
Every day one of us paid for the food, the seven of us, and this prison

1016
01:05:17,028 --> 01:05:25,026
It seemed that the jailers, the emir, and the rest of the group bringing food were all from poor families

1017
01:05:25,106 --> 01:05:27,299
When they brought food, they gave it to the other prisoners

1018
01:05:27,324 --> 01:05:31,072
Because the prison had two sections: one for the rest of the prisoners and one just for us seven

1019
01:05:31,104 --> 01:05:35,854
We seven took turns. For example, if it was my turn, my wife knew that today was my turn

1020
01:05:36,198 --> 01:05:42,024
She brought food for me and for the guards, like fried chicken one day and grilled kebab another

1021
01:05:42,547 --> 01:05:48,930
She brought us ready meals from the market, and there was plenty. My turn came once a week since we were 7 people

1022
01:05:48,955 --> 01:05:51,923
Every day food was paid for by one of us, so my turn came once a week to bring the food

1023
01:05:51,948 --> 01:05:57,213
The food bill was about 75 to 100 thousand per month, all ready food from the market for us

1024
01:05:57,393 --> 01:06:00,704
And the ISIS members started sitting and spending evenings with us

1025
01:06:00,729 --> 01:06:04,988
They chatted with us, and we bought nuts and soft drinks, though we were shackled

1026
01:06:05,690 --> 01:06:08,776
They trusted us and learned our story

1027
01:06:08,987 --> 01:06:12,963
They told us, “Your charge is collaboration with the Global Coalition, and you’re sentenced to execution”

1028
01:06:13,065 --> 01:06:16,182
That actually helped us a lot in planning our escape

1029
01:06:16,383 --> 01:06:23,408
Interviewer: Didn’t you try, for example, to pay them money to get out of prison?

1030
01:06:23,815 --> 01:06:28,002
Interviewer: Many people paid and got released, even those sentenced to execution

1031
01:06:28,027 --> 01:06:31,971
I was well known, one of the familiar figures

1032
01:06:32,135 --> 01:06:36,877
I was chained with iron shackles, and it was impossible for me to pay money

1033
01:06:37,315 --> 01:06:44,189
To escape, break free from the chains, and leave the room. There were 3 locked iron doors

1034
01:06:44,354 --> 01:06:49,518
But once, we had a jailer who wasn’t just a jailer—he was also an emir in ISIS

1035
01:06:49,846 --> 01:06:51,744
In the Mafarq al-Jazra area

1036
01:06:53,112 --> 01:06:58,531
They said he was one of the “Kanas” family. I remember only his nickname, I forgot his name, but he was a good man too

1037
01:06:58,846 --> 01:07:02,007
In the morning, the emir Abu Saqr from the al-Dabba family came

1038
01:07:02,158 --> 01:07:03,990
He was on morning duty as the emir

1039
01:07:04,221 --> 01:07:08,371
At night, the shift changed. That man left around sunset, and another took over

1040
01:07:08,396 --> 01:07:10,471
He was from Mafarq al-Jazra and was well known

1041
01:07:10,721 --> 01:07:12,963
He told me he was married to two women

1042
01:07:14,026 --> 01:07:20,416
Sometimes he came and sat with us, but ISIS put him under surveillance because he was kind and sympathetic to prisoners

1043
01:07:21,783 --> 01:07:26,120
We paid him 7 million to bring us just a piece of a saw

1044
01:07:26,512 --> 01:07:28,003
So we could escape, we told him

1045
01:07:28,347 --> 01:07:32,244
We’re 7 prisoners. If you can just bring us a small metal saw blade

1046
01:07:32,643 --> 01:07:37,502
Just so we could cut the big lock hanging on the wall

1047
01:07:39,539 --> 01:07:40,682
To escape

1048
01:07:40,707 --> 01:07:45,760
We told him each of us would give you one million. He said, “ISIS will kill me.” We said, “You’ll escape with us”

1049
01:07:46,307 --> 01:07:50,612
Praise God, he was supposed to bring us the saw blade

1050
01:07:50,924 --> 01:07:55,002
But the next day, they arrested him

1051
01:07:55,330 --> 01:07:59,688
They transferred him. We didn’t know whether he was detained or relocated, but we never saw him again after that

1052
01:08:00,208 --> 01:08:01,807
And we never learned what happened

1053
01:08:06,838 --> 01:08:08,487
When they tried to bargain with me

1054
01:08:09,244 --> 01:08:12,019
They bargained with me a lot, even the well-known emirs

1055
01:08:12,877 --> 01:08:14,526
There were prominent figures among them

1056
01:08:15,901 --> 01:08:22,282
Specifically, one from the al-Amer family and one from the al-Mukhtar family bargained with me

1057
01:08:22,941 --> 01:08:25,641
They told me, “Bring us fertilizer”

1058
01:08:25,938 --> 01:08:32,196
Fertilizer 33, the one they use to make explosives

1059
01:08:32,860 --> 01:08:37,110
They bargained with me to bring cigarettes and hide the fertilizer inside them for them

1060
01:08:37,282 --> 01:08:41,297
Many people bargained with me, not just them

1061
01:08:41,547 --> 01:08:47,501
Even Abu Seif himself bargained with me to work with him

1062
01:08:47,977 --> 01:08:51,416
And to pass on reports and information to him

1063
01:08:51,968 --> 01:08:54,233
He told me, “Whatever you want in return, you’ll get it”

1064
01:08:54,258 --> 01:08:57,704
I told him, “I’m not that kind of man”

1065
01:08:58,102 --> 01:09:01,697
That’s when Abu Seif began to hate me

1066
01:09:02,540 --> 01:09:05,204
His eyes turned red with anger toward me

1067
01:09:06,596 --> 01:09:07,796
And one time

1068
01:09:10,149 --> 01:09:12,111
There’s a story I want to tell

1069
01:09:13,385 --> 01:09:17,594
ISIS planted a man with disabled children and placed him next to me

1070
01:09:18,617 --> 01:09:23,604
Pretending he was wanted by ISIS for a rifle he couldn’t afford, and he had disabled children

1071
01:09:23,828 --> 01:09:26,977
He lived next to me and became very close to me

1072
01:09:28,266 --> 01:09:31,508
He grew close like one of my sons, and I pitied him

1073
01:09:32,522 --> 01:09:36,974
Even my family felt sorry for him and cried, and we bought him things for his home

1074
01:09:37,086 --> 01:09:40,969
When my family went shopping for bread or vegetables

1075
01:09:40,994 --> 01:09:43,203
They bought things for his kids like for ours

1076
01:09:43,227 --> 01:09:46,602
I told my wife, “That man’s home is like a second home to me”

1077
01:09:46,750 --> 01:09:48,687
Because he was sick and unemployed

1078
01:09:49,352 --> 01:09:54,453
His family did nothing, and he had disabled children

1079
01:09:54,478 --> 01:09:57,553
He spent about a month and a half trying to work with me

1080
01:09:57,578 --> 01:10:00,781
I told him, “Stay home. I’ll cover all your kids’ expenses”

1081
01:10:00,789 --> 01:10:01,804
One time

1082
01:10:03,726 --> 01:10:06,945
I was sitting on the roof smoking a waterpipe

1083
01:10:07,734 --> 01:10:12,718
I saw the man collapse unconscious. My brother was with me; we carried him to the hospital

1084
01:10:14,313 --> 01:10:19,804
Apparently, he had a neurological illness. I didn’t know what it was; I thought he was dead

1085
01:10:20,399 --> 01:10:24,945
He knew I traded in cigarettes but didn’t know where the main warehouses were

1086
01:10:25,492 --> 01:10:30,538
When he saw my kindness and my faith, he loved me and refused to betray me

1087
01:10:31,280 --> 01:10:32,648
I took him to the hospital

1088
01:10:33,046 --> 01:10:34,600
In less than 10 minutes

1089
01:10:37,749 --> 01:10:41,874
All the emirs in the province came—at least the ones I knew

1090
01:10:42,319 --> 01:10:45,130
They had very long beards, though mine reached my navel

1091
01:10:45,155 --> 01:10:47,288
But mine was nothing compared to theirs

1092
01:10:47,507 --> 01:10:52,116
They were all emirs, migrants from Iraq

1093
01:10:52,765 --> 01:11:00,209
Migrants from various nationalities, including well-known migrant women and high-ranking emirs I never imagined

1094
01:11:00,608 --> 01:11:02,804
They came to check on him. At that moment, I

1095
01:11:03,210 --> 01:11:05,388
Was leaning against the wall, then I went down

1096
01:11:05,413 --> 01:11:08,677
I collapsed from fear; my legs couldn’t hold me

1097
01:11:08,702 --> 01:11:12,482
I sat on the floor like that. My life was ruined

1098
01:11:12,507 --> 01:11:14,709
Not just ruined—they were going to kill me too

1099
01:11:14,734 --> 01:11:16,669
For me, I was already finished

1100
01:11:16,694 --> 01:11:19,734
I sat there and wanted to stand up, but I couldn’t

1101
01:11:20,444 --> 01:11:23,109
They came to me and asked about the man’s condition

1102
01:11:23,134 --> 01:11:27,523
From time to time, someone would come to me. All of them had long beards and held high positions

1103
01:11:29,343 --> 01:11:31,804
When I saw the emirs

1104
01:11:33,937 --> 01:11:35,359
My tears started to fall

1105
01:11:37,163 --> 01:11:44,062
The man, who was in intensive care, turned his face toward me and looked at me. I wiped my tears like this, and he saw me

1106
01:11:46,648 --> 01:11:48,484
He gestured to his wife

1107
01:11:50,663 --> 01:11:52,530
He pointed at me, so his wife came over

1108
01:11:54,562 --> 01:11:56,624
She said, “What’s wrong? Why are you crying?”

1109
01:11:57,030 --> 01:12:00,015
I told her quietly, “Did I do something to you?”

1110
01:12:00,499 --> 01:12:03,562
My voice wouldn’t come out because I was completely exhausted inside the hospital

1111
01:12:04,577 --> 01:12:07,109
I said, “Please, I beg you, help me get out of the room”

1112
01:12:07,599 --> 01:12:09,069
When I stood up like this

1113
01:12:10,217 --> 01:12:11,905
The Emir of the Islamic Police arrived

1114
01:12:11,930 --> 01:12:16,710
His base was in the Mefraq al-Jazra area, and his name was Muhammad Tawhid, known as Abu Tawhid

1115
01:12:16,735 --> 01:12:20,650
He had a black SUV, like Murad Alamdar’s car from the Turkish series

1116
01:12:20,675 --> 01:12:24,640
Everyone knew that when Muhammad Tawhid arrived, it was as if Murad Alamdar himself had come

1117
01:12:25,124 --> 01:12:26,765
Then Muhammad Tawhid came

1118
01:12:27,554 --> 01:12:29,648
When I stood up, he looked at me

1119
01:12:30,359 --> 01:12:32,089
He said, “Welcome, welcome”

1120
01:12:32,577 --> 01:12:34,405
“Welcome, Talal al-Shuweimi”

1121
01:12:34,632 --> 01:12:39,898
I knew him, so I said softly, “Sheikh, do you know me?” I was honestly terrified

1122
01:12:41,515 --> 01:12:42,703
He asked, “Why are you crying?”

1123
01:12:42,985 --> 01:12:44,665
I said, “Because my friend is sick”

1124
01:12:45,156 --> 01:12:49,262
I told him that, hoping it would give me a chance to leave the room

1125
01:12:50,726 --> 01:12:52,609
He said, “Is there anyone who doesn’t know you?”

1126
01:12:55,937 --> 01:12:59,112
“You’re the biggest dealer of vice in town. How could anyone not know you?”

1127
01:13:00,218 --> 01:13:02,843
He said, “For your information, we’re friends and relatives”

1128
01:13:03,545 --> 01:13:05,374
“We’ve been in touch with you many times”

1129
01:13:06,288 --> 01:13:12,194
At that moment, the patient’s wife was holding my hand because I had no strength left to stand, so I squeezed her hand

1130
01:13:12,304 --> 01:13:14,648
She said, “Excuse me, Sheikh”

1131
01:13:15,690 --> 01:13:20,025
“This man came with us and saved my husband. He’s our neighbor.” Then she took me outside

1132
01:13:22,148 --> 01:13:24,093
What can I say?

1133
01:13:24,118 --> 01:13:29,601
That man knew everything about me, how much I earned each day, and how many millions I made

1134
01:13:30,187 --> 01:13:35,304
Sometimes I would call in front of him and order 200 or 300 boxes of cigarettes a day

1135
01:13:35,937 --> 01:13:39,874
I asked her, “Did I wrong you in any way? Did I ever harm you?”

1136
01:13:40,523 --> 01:13:45,552
“You came into my house, and I came into yours. You know there’s no need to remind you of that”

1137
01:13:45,577 --> 01:13:47,655
She said, “God willing, no one will harm you”

1138
01:13:48,894 --> 01:13:51,484
Anyway, I just told her, “Please help me escape from the hospital”

1139
01:13:52,265 --> 01:13:55,393
At that time, I was driving a Mercedes 600 “Shabah”

1140
01:13:56,691 --> 01:13:59,218
When I left the Modern Medicine Hospital

1141
01:14:01,530 --> 01:14:05,198
I ran down a slope in front of the hospital

1142
01:14:05,995 --> 01:14:09,939
As I reached the bottom, a car suddenly appeared in front of me, and I almost crashed into it

1143
01:14:09,964 --> 01:14:13,215
My own car was parked in front of the hospital. I had used it to drive the patient there

1144
01:14:13,597 --> 01:14:18,237
I jumped into a Saba taxi and escaped

1145
01:14:18,534 --> 01:14:22,948
When I got home, my kids asked, “Where’s your car?”

1146
01:14:23,290 --> 01:14:28,790
That’s when I realized, from fear and panic, that I’d left my car in front of the Modern Medicine Hospital

1147
01:14:29,287 --> 01:14:30,831
Imagine that situation

1148
01:14:32,612 --> 01:14:37,933
I told my wife, “Gather all the money we have. We’re leaving”

1149
01:14:38,938 --> 01:14:43,883
My wife started collecting the money and cash. I didn’t sleep until 3 a.m.

1150
01:14:44,399 --> 01:14:46,618
I locked the doors and sat on the stairs

1151
01:14:46,829 --> 01:14:49,974
We had a big chandelier above the stairs, surrounded by a railing

1152
01:14:49,999 --> 01:14:53,100
I sat there, and somehow, I dozed off

1153
01:14:53,454 --> 01:14:55,288
Then the man knocked on the door

1154
01:14:56,321 --> 01:14:58,797
He still had the IV drip attached, and his wife brought him to me

1155
01:14:59,126 --> 01:15:02,985
I looked down from above and saw him. I said, “Who’s at the door?” He answered, “It’s Abu [name withheld]”

1156
01:15:04,914 --> 01:15:08,618
I told my wife, “Open the door for him.” My family was awake. We were about to flee

1157
01:15:10,203 --> 01:15:12,524
She opened the door, and he came in and sat down

1158
01:15:14,063 --> 01:15:15,626
I said, “What do you want from me, brother?”

1159
01:15:17,657 --> 01:15:25,579
I meant, ask for anything you want, and I’ll give it to you. Just let me and my children get out of here alive

1160
01:15:27,273 --> 01:15:29,587
The man—may God bless him—had mercy on me

1161
01:15:30,428 --> 01:15:34,378
He said, “You’re a good man. You have faith in God, and you’re a decent person”

1162
01:15:34,403 --> 01:15:36,849
“If I stay here, they’ll harm me”

1163
01:15:37,248 --> 01:15:39,906
He was from the al-Akkal family of the Naeimi clan

1164
01:15:40,716 --> 01:15:46,169
He had infiltrated me and discovered who I was. He was from the village of al-Akkal but not one of their own

1165
01:15:47,771 --> 01:15:51,568
They brought him in pretending he was poor. Those who sent him were senior leaders in the organization

1166
01:15:51,593 --> 01:15:56,772
He told me, “When they brought me in, it was to bring them your head and slaughter you. But you welcomed me into your home”

1167
01:16:00,560 --> 01:16:05,192
In the last moment, he changed his mind and said, “Forgive me, brother. Please forgive me”

1168
01:16:05,646 --> 01:16:07,856
I asked, “Do you want money?” He said, “I don’t need money”

1169
01:16:08,826 --> 01:16:10,349
“It was all a setup against you”

1170
01:16:11,342 --> 01:16:12,818
And that’s the story

1171
01:16:13,099 --> 01:16:16,107
I stood up, kissed his head, and said, “May God guide you”

1172
01:16:16,685 --> 01:16:19,099
He said, “I’m sick, and I have disabled children”

1173
01:16:19,568 --> 01:16:23,937
Previously, I had paid for a rifle he owed the al-Akkal sons

1174
01:16:23,962 --> 01:16:26,980
Every day they’d bring him and humiliate him over that rifle’s price

1175
01:16:27,106 --> 01:16:29,588
I paid him 120,000 SYP for it

1176
01:16:29,613 --> 01:16:32,839
At that time, 1 USD equaled 450 SYP

1177
01:16:33,638 --> 01:16:37,013
I told my wife, “We can’t stay here any longer”

1178
01:16:37,920 --> 01:16:39,287
We stayed a bit longer

1179
01:16:40,232 --> 01:16:43,999
I said, “We’ll leave at sunrise. There’s heavy security on the organization’s checkpoints”

1180
01:16:44,989 --> 01:16:49,410
I told her, “Prepare my hookah.” I sat smoking while the kids had breakfast

1181
01:16:49,779 --> 01:16:53,412
Then I said, “Go check the street. See if anyone’s there so we can get in the car and flee”

1182
01:16:54,131 --> 01:16:58,504
She saw that our neighbor’s door was open and said, “Abu [name withheld]’s door is open”

1183
01:16:58,529 --> 01:17:03,803
When I went over, I saw he had taken his kids and left. May God guide and forgive him

1184
01:17:03,828 --> 01:17:08,748
That was one of the moments that truly showed how terrified I was of the organization

1185
01:17:09,553 --> 01:17:15,396
There were many other incidents. If I were to talk about them, it would take me three months and I still wouldn’t finish

1186
01:17:19,967 --> 01:17:21,810
One day, the organization took me

1187
01:17:24,459 --> 01:17:29,341
Abu Seif came to me. The first time, he came with Abu Khaled al-Idlibi and other men

1188
01:17:31,904 --> 01:17:32,904
They took me away

1189
01:17:34,162 --> 01:17:37,122
They said, “Come with us to carry out your sentence”

1190
01:17:40,482 --> 01:17:41,482
Of course

1191
01:17:42,732 --> 01:17:45,412
They took me along with six other men

1192
01:17:48,724 --> 01:17:52,326
Among them was a man named Abdul Karim al-Ghaffaf

1193
01:17:52,881 --> 01:17:54,099
He was from the al-Marandi clan

1194
01:17:55,811 --> 01:18:00,654
He was one of my uncles, and his charge was adopting Shia beliefs

1195
01:18:02,256 --> 01:18:04,513
An old man, about 80 years old

1196
01:18:05,114 --> 01:18:08,489
There was also another man from the al-Bu Assaf clan named Yasin al-Yasin

1197
01:18:08,514 --> 01:18:09,514
Anyway

1198
01:18:10,303 --> 01:18:11,740
There were six men, and I was the seventh

1199
01:18:12,459 --> 01:18:17,482
They took me in a car, and I felt that we had left the city

1200
01:18:24,490 --> 01:18:28,763
They made us get out, and there was a cool breeze in the air

1201
01:18:29,146 --> 01:18:31,724
They made us kneel on our knees

1202
01:18:33,108 --> 01:18:34,788
And when they made us kneel

1203
01:18:36,935 --> 01:18:39,810
One of the emirs said, “Remove the cloth blindfold from Talal al-Shuweimi’s eyes”

1204
01:18:41,888 --> 01:18:43,357
They removed the blindfold from my eyes

1205
01:18:45,185 --> 01:18:50,302
Then I looked to my right and left and saw that everyone was lined up on both sides

1206
01:18:51,606 --> 01:18:55,029
They told them, “You did this and that, say the two testimonies”

1207
01:18:57,411 --> 01:19:02,373
So they recited the testimonies, and each one was shot in the head

1208
01:19:03,129 --> 01:19:08,088
I looked around and the place was full of trees—it used to be a Baath Pioneers camp

1209
01:19:08,113 --> 01:19:14,604
When we were kids, we used to go there in summer for school camps during the Assad regime

1210
01:19:16,580 --> 01:19:18,762
One of them said to me, “Talal al-Shuweimi”

1211
01:19:22,293 --> 01:19:23,493
What do you want?

1212
01:19:24,105 --> 01:19:27,855
I said, I don’t want anything. You brought me here and sentenced me to execution

1213
01:19:30,785 --> 01:19:31,824
He said to me

1214
01:19:34,011 --> 01:19:37,499
They removed the cloth blindfold from my eyes so I could see around me

1215
01:19:39,043 --> 01:19:45,324
Among them were well-known people—some of the senior figures in the ISIS state

1216
01:19:45,871 --> 01:19:51,605
High-ranking figures who are still alive today

1217
01:19:56,699 --> 01:19:57,700
He said to me

1218
01:19:58,254 --> 01:20:00,518
Now we’ll carry out the sentence and get rid of you

1219
01:20:00,543 --> 01:20:01,964
Then another masked man came

1220
01:20:04,824 --> 01:20:05,964
And said to me

1221
01:20:08,800 --> 01:20:10,113
What is your last wish?

1222
01:20:15,395 --> 01:20:16,395
At that moment

1223
01:20:47,027 --> 01:20:48,932
I told him, to speak with my children

1224
01:20:51,699 --> 01:20:53,627
He placed the pistol on my head

1225
01:21:02,386 --> 01:21:04,683
He said, “Say the two testimonies,” so I did

1226
01:21:07,596 --> 01:21:08,596
Then he struck me

1227
01:21:09,143 --> 01:21:13,511
As if he hit me in the head, but he fired the shot beside my ear

1228
01:21:16,548 --> 01:21:20,298
When he fired beside my ear, out of terror and horror

1229
01:21:22,306 --> 01:21:24,818
My hands were tied behind my back, and I fell to the ground

1230
01:21:25,517 --> 01:21:28,197
From the terror of it—it was like an American movie

1231
01:21:28,759 --> 01:21:29,853
I mean, something

1232
01:21:30,308 --> 01:21:34,884
Something indescribable, something even the Jews wouldn’t envy you for

1233
01:21:35,447 --> 01:21:42,508
Nor the Christians, nor Israel, nor even black devils would wish to see you in such a position

1234
01:21:42,533 --> 01:21:44,204
They wouldn’t even gloat over you

1235
01:21:49,650 --> 01:21:55,728
The last time I was imprisoned—as I said earlier—they transferred me from one prison to another

1236
01:21:56,590 --> 01:21:58,204
To a prison hidden in a corner

1237
01:21:58,759 --> 01:22:02,628
Sadly, that prison was across from my mother’s house

1238
01:22:03,392 --> 01:22:05,308
My mother’s name is Zahia

1239
01:22:05,712 --> 01:22:08,742
And one of the emirs, named Muhammad al-Abadi

1240
01:22:08,767 --> 01:22:11,907
Used to tell me, “Zahia’s son, I saw Zahia walking in the garden”

1241
01:22:11,932 --> 01:22:14,896
We were on the second floor, and he said, “I saw your mother”

1242
01:22:15,587 --> 01:22:17,095
The man was joking with me

1243
01:22:18,236 --> 01:22:22,017
We escaped from the prison during the days of the Euphrates Dam collapse in Raqqa

1244
01:22:22,931 --> 01:22:26,876
There were several of us, and that same man was with us

1245
01:22:27,572 --> 01:22:29,036
His name was Abu Muhammad al-Abadi

1246
01:22:29,490 --> 01:22:31,490
May God bless and reward him

1247
01:22:32,157 --> 01:22:34,095
We made a hole in the prison wall

1248
01:22:34,120 --> 01:22:41,715
He escaped with us, helped us, and watched the road. There were seven of us, and a car was waiting

1249
01:22:42,613 --> 01:22:44,717
We escaped by car, the seven of us

1250
01:22:50,941 --> 01:22:53,838
As for me, there’s a saying: they asked the nail, “Why did you go into the wall?”

1251
01:22:53,863 --> 01:22:57,496
He answered, “From how much they hit my head”

1252
01:22:57,521 --> 01:23:03,011
I didn’t sell cigarettes by choice, but I was an employee

1253
01:23:03,863 --> 01:23:06,980
My salary was 12,000 Syrian Lira, working in the Water Authority

1254
01:23:07,597 --> 01:23:13,102
After I started working, Air Force Intelligence raided my house and detained my brother, taking him to Sednaya Prison

1255
01:23:15,261 --> 01:23:19,465
When they raided my place and I fled, I had 10 children

1256
01:23:20,746 --> 01:23:22,624
They needed food and bread

1257
01:23:22,785 --> 01:23:27,613
I bought a taxi without papers and drove it, but the income wasn’t enough

1258
01:23:27,925 --> 01:23:31,558
And cigarette trade wasn’t punishable by execution or anything like that

1259
01:23:31,583 --> 01:23:37,002
But the organization imposed execution on us, even though it wasn’t for cigarette trade

1260
01:23:37,080 --> 01:23:39,150
Their judgments became vindictive

1261
01:23:39,307 --> 01:23:44,791
They invented charges—collaboration, cigarettes, ammunition—just to sentence us to execution

1262
01:23:44,854 --> 01:23:50,330
I was forced into cigarette trade. I have children and pay rent for two houses

1263
01:23:50,642 --> 01:23:55,794
Every day I’d buy bread for 2,000 or 3,000 Syrian Lira, and there was no other work

1264
01:23:55,939 --> 01:23:59,406
With the organization, either you join them or remain jobless

1265
01:23:59,689 --> 01:24:01,728
So how could I feed my children?

1266
01:24:01,955 --> 01:24:06,517
Should I trade cigarettes to earn a living and feed them, or let them starve to death?

1267
01:24:10,806 --> 01:24:13,019
Prison had a huge impact on me

1268
01:24:14,580 --> 01:24:16,198
When I first escaped from prison

1269
01:24:16,582 --> 01:24:17,916
I started crying

1270
01:24:18,885 --> 01:24:25,720
Tears of joy, not sadness

1271
01:24:25,792 --> 01:24:28,119
I began kissing the ground

1272
01:24:28,572 --> 01:24:34,517
I looked up to God Almighty, crying and shouting, breathing in the air

1273
01:24:35,158 --> 01:24:38,775
So many things happened to me

1274
01:24:38,800 --> 01:24:42,217
Prison affected me deeply—like forgetfulness, for example

1275
01:24:42,689 --> 01:24:45,213
It left me with memory loss

1276
01:24:46,345 --> 01:24:50,970
Tragic events that scarred me

1277
01:24:51,291 --> 01:24:54,892
In my life, I never held hatred toward anyone

1278
01:24:55,306 --> 01:24:57,798
But they made my heart hard

1279
01:24:57,939 --> 01:25:03,025
They killed the mercy inside me as a human being belonging to humanity

1280
01:25:03,556 --> 01:25:09,101
They ignored so many rights—human rights, and my rights as a Muslim

1281
01:25:09,705 --> 01:25:14,063
As a father and provider for a family, for example

1282
01:25:14,142 --> 01:25:16,189
They stripped the mercy from within me

1283
01:25:16,666 --> 01:25:18,508
There are still many things inside me

1284
01:25:18,533 --> 01:25:25,817
ISIS affected me deeply, and I still suffer from what’s called forgetfulness

1285
01:25:26,220 --> 01:25:30,838
On top of that, the greatest hardship remains—that only God provides and sustains us

1286
01:25:30,970 --> 01:25:33,611
God Almighty is the Provider

1287
01:25:34,556 --> 01:25:37,547
For me, ISIS destroyed my life

1288
01:25:37,891 --> 01:25:40,806
Why am I still struggling today to buy bread?

1289
01:25:42,041 --> 01:25:46,635
Why am I looking for a job as a taxi driver for daily pay?

1290
01:25:49,275 --> 01:25:50,275
What’s the reason?

1291
01:25:52,751 --> 01:25:54,063
Because of an ignorant man

1292
01:25:55,588 --> 01:25:57,088
Because of an infidel

1293
01:25:57,861 --> 01:25:59,908
Who should be in prison for two or three years

1294
01:26:00,416 --> 01:26:03,127
God willing, may the Almighty take from my life

1295
01:26:04,697 --> 01:26:05,916
And give it to his

1296
01:26:07,431 --> 01:26:11,986
Just so I live long enough until he gets out of prison, to see him even for one hour

1297
01:26:13,049 --> 01:26:14,720
To settle my score with him

1298
01:26:15,306 --> 01:26:18,344
An eye for an eye, a tooth for a tooth, and the aggressor is the unjust one

1299
01:26:18,486 --> 01:26:20,690
Everyone dies once

1300
01:26:20,970 --> 01:26:26,862
Better that than dying every hour before your children

1301
01:26:54,252 --> 01:26:57,439
I ask God that he come out of prison, God willing

1302
01:26:59,275 --> 01:27:01,817
And may God keep me alive for you Abu Seif

1303
01:27:02,174 --> 01:27:03,174
God willing

1304
01:27:04,955 --> 01:27:07,791
And I ask that God not let me live if He lets you live

1305
01:27:09,056 --> 01:27:12,116
May God not have mercy on me if I spare you Abu Seif

1306
01:27:12,984 --> 01:27:14,010
If I knew

1307
01:27:14,970 --> 01:27:17,291
that all the world's intelligence services protect you

1308
01:27:18,072 --> 01:27:24,492
The Coalition, Israel, Bashar al-Assad, and your Baghdadi, even if all of them protect you

1309
01:27:24,517 --> 01:27:27,398
If I knew how to become a bomb to blow you up, I would definitely do it
